{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781756713890,"sessionID":"ses_1270761dbffecw7Dfym5Wp50VJ","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_JamD6B2OS2oonSM2h5or41Z1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"phase_init|phase_main_loop|phase_synthesis|resolveArtifactRoot|fanout_lineage_artifact_dir|artifact_dir|reduce-state","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets","include":"deep_review_auto.yaml"},"output":"Found 40 matches\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml:\n  Line 41:   trigger: \"At workflow START, before phase_init\"\n\n  Line 89:   packet_dir: \"{artifact_dir}\"\n\n  Line 92:   config: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-config.json\"\n\n  Line 93:   state_log: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-state.jsonl\"\n\n  Line 94:   findings_registry: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-findings-registry.json\"\n\n  Line 95:   strategy: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md\"\n\n  Line 96:   dashboard: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-dashboard.md\"\n\n  Line 97:   pause_sentinel: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-review-pause\"\n\n  Line 98:   lock_file: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-review.lock\"\n\n  Line 99:   prompt_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/prompts\"\n\n  Line 100:   iteration_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations\"\n\n  Line 101:   iteration_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md\"\n\n  Line 105:   delta_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas\"\n\n  Line 106:   delta_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas/iter-{NNN}.jsonl\"\n\n  Line 107:   review_output: \"{artifact_dir}/review-report.md\"\n\n  Line 108:   resource_map_output: \"{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md\"\n\n  Line 119:     branch_on: \"config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir\"\n\n  Line 122:         artifact_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n\n  Line 123:         artifact_root_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n\n  Line 125:         artifact_archive_root: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}/_archive\"\n\n  Line 127:       command: \"node -e \\\"const { resolveArtifactRoot } = require('.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs'); console.log(JSON.stringify(resolveArtifactRoot('{spec_folder}', 'review')));\\\"\"\n\n  Line 131:         - artifact_dir: \"Resolved review packet directory for this target\"\n\n  Line 135:     description: \"Spawn fan-out lineages; skip and proceed to phase_init normally when single-executor\"\n\n  Line 139:       isolated sub-packet under {artifact_dir}/lineages/{label}/.\n\n  Line 140:       After all lineages complete, jump directly to phase_synthesis — skip phase_init and\n\n  Line 141:       phase_main_loop entirely (those are the single-executor path). The merge step in\n\n  Line 142:       phase_synthesis will consolidate results across all lineages.\n\n  Line 152:             --base-artifact-dir {artifact_dir}\n\n  Line 165:               config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir: {artifact_dir}/lineages/{lineage.label}\n\n  Line 174:   phase_init:\n\n  Line 284:           skip_to: phase_synthesis\n\n  Line 646:           skip_to: phase_synthesis\n\n  Line 1010:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder}\"\n\n  Line 1119:   phase_synthesis:\n\n  Line 1129:             --artifact-dir {artifact_dir}\n\n  Line 1223:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder} --emit-resource-map\"\n\n  Line 1301:       step_stage_artifact_dir:\n\n  Line 1302:         action: \"Stage all skill-owned artifacts under artifact_dir for the operator's next git commit\"\n\n  Line 1304:         note: \"Skill-owned contract fix (028): without this stage step, operators who do `git add review-report.md` lose the iteration trail (iterations/, deltas/, state.jsonl, strategy, findings-registry, etc.). Staging the whole artifact_dir keeps the audit trail intact. Operators retain commit authority and can `git restore --staged {path}` to unstage anything before commit. Failure is non-fatal — log warning and continue.\"\n\n  Line 1305:         on_fail: \"Log warning. Do not block synthesis. The artifact_dir may be outside a git repo (e.g., temp test fixture) which is a valid case.\"\n","metadata":{"matches":40,"truncated":false},"title":"phase_init|phase_main_loop|phase_synthesis|resolveArtifactRoot|fanout_lineage_artifact_dir|artifact_dir|reduce-state","time":{"start":1781756713870,"end":1781756713889}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0606ee1f4d679b5d016a337329d60481918c2ec9d3a4465d48"}},"id":"prt_ed8f9db82001u6jAYlNrFTcupv","sessionID":"ses_1270761dbffecw7Dfym5Wp50VJ","messageID":"msg_ed8f9ac4b0015LFGMJKspDbNZp"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781756713943,"sessionID":"ses_1270761dbffecw7Dfym5Wp50VJ","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_8O6zfqgyJeidVAqW9WvDg96a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_strategy.md","offset":1,"limit":2000},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_strategy.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Review Strategy Template\n3: description: Runtime template copied to review/ during initialization to track review progress, dimension coverage, findings, and outcomes across iterations.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"deep review strategy template\"\n6:   - \"review dimension tracking\"\n7:   - \"exhausted review approaches\"\n8:   - \"review session tracking\"\n9: importance_tier: normal\n10: contextType: planning\n11: ---\n12: \n13: # Deep Review Strategy - Session Tracking Template\n14: \n15: Runtime template copied into the resolved `{artifact_dir}/` during initialization. Tracks review progress across iterations.\n16: \n17: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n18: \n19: ### Purpose\n20: \n21: Serves as the \"persistent brain\" for a deep review session. Records which dimensions remain, what was found (P0/P1/P2), what review approaches worked or failed, and where to focus next. Read by the orchestrator and agents at every iteration.\n22: \n23: ### Usage\n24: \n25: - **Init:** Orchestrator copies this template to `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md` and populates Topic, Review Dimensions, Known Context, and Review Boundaries from config and memory context.\n26: - **Per iteration:** Agent reads Next Focus, reviews the assigned dimension/files, updates findings, marks dimensions complete, and sets new Next Focus.\n27: - **Mutability:** Mutable, updated by both orchestrator and agents throughout the session.\n28: - **Protection:** None (shared mutable state). Orchestrator validates consistency on resume.\n29: - **Ownership:** Machine-managed metrics and coverage blocks are wrapped in explicit ownership markers. Human commentary and operator overrides live outside those markers.\n30: \n31: ---\n32: \n33: ## 2. TOPIC\n34: [Review target description from config -- set during initialization]\n35: \n36: ---\n37: \n38: ## 3. REVIEW DIMENSIONS (remaining)\n39: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n40: - [ ] D1 Correctness, Logic errors, off-by-one, wrong return types, broken invariants\n41: - [ ] D2 Security, Injection, auth bypass, secrets exposure, unsafe deserialization\n42: - [ ] D3 Traceability, Spec/code alignment, checklist evidence, cross-reference integrity\n43: - [ ] D4 Maintainability, Patterns, clarity, documentation quality, safe follow-on change cost\n44: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n45: \n46: ---\n47: \n48: ## 4. NON-GOALS\n49: [What this review session is NOT trying to assess -- populated during initialization]\n50: \n51: ---\n52: \n53: ## 5. STOP CONDITIONS\n54: [Explicit conditions beyond convergence that should end the session -- populated during initialization]\n55: \n56: ---\n57: \n58: ## 6. COMPLETED DIMENSIONS\n59: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n60: [None yet -- populated as iterations complete dimension reviews]\n61: \n62: | Dimension | Verdict | Iteration | Summary |\n63: |-----------|---------|-----------|---------|\n64: | [D1 Correctness] | [PASS/CONDITIONAL/FAIL] | [N] | [1-sentence result] |\n65: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n66: \n67: ---\n68: \n69: ## 7. RUNNING FINDINGS\n70: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n71: - **P0 (Critical):** 0 active\n72: - **P1 (Major):** 0 active\n73: - **P2 (Minor):** 0 active\n74: - **Delta this iteration:** +0 P0, +0 P1, +0 P2\n75: \n76: [Findings are tracked in `deep-review-findings-registry.json`. This section provides a running count summary updated after each iteration.]\n77: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n78: \n79: ---\n80: \n81: ## 8. WHAT WORKED\n82: [First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n83: - [Approach]: [Why it worked] (iteration N)\n84: \n85: ---\n86: \n87: ## 9. WHAT FAILED\n88: [First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n89: - [Approach]: [Why it failed] (iteration N)\n90: \n91: ---\n92: \n93: ## 10. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n94: [Populated when a review approach has been tried from multiple angles without yielding new findings]\n95: \n96: ### [Category Name] -- BLOCKED (iteration N, N attempts)\n97: - What was tried: [specific review approaches attempted]\n98: - Why blocked: [root cause of exhaustion]\n99: - Do NOT retry: [explicit prohibition]\n100: \n101: ### [Category Name] -- PRODUCTIVE (iteration N)\n102: - What worked: [successful review approaches in this category]\n103: - Prefer for: [related dimensions where this category may help]\n104: \n105: ---\n106: \n107: ## 11. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n108: [Review angles that were investigated and definitively eliminated -- consolidated from iteration dead-end data]\n109: - [Approach]: [Why ruled out] (iteration N, evidence: [source])\n110: \n111: ---\n112: \n113: ## 12. NEXT FOCUS\n114: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n115: [Recommended focus area for the next iteration -- updated at end of each iteration. Includes target dimension and/or specific files to review.]\n116: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n117: \n118: ---\n119: \n120: ## 13. KNOWN CONTEXT\n121: [Populated during initialization from memory_context() results, if any prior work exists]\n122: \n123: ---\n124: \n125: ## 14. CROSS-REFERENCE STATUS\n126: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n127: [Alignment checks completed across core and overlay protocols]\n128: \n129: | Protocol | Level | Status | Iteration | Notes |\n130: |----------|-------|--------|-----------|-------|\n131: | `spec_code` | core | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked] | [N] | [details] |\n132: | `checklist_evidence` | core | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked] | [N] | [details] |\n133: | `skill_agent` | overlay | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked/notApplicable] | [N] | [details] |\n134: | `agent_cross_runtime` | overlay | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked/notApplicable] | [N] | [details] |\n135: | `feature_catalog_code` | overlay | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked/notApplicable] | [N] | [details] |\n136: | `playbook_capability` | overlay | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked/notApplicable] | [N] | [details] |\n137: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n138: \n139: ---\n140: \n141: ## 15. FILES UNDER REVIEW\n142: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n143: [Per-file coverage state table -- populated during initialization from scope discovery]\n144: \n145: | File | Dimensions Reviewed | Last Iteration | Findings | Status |\n146: |------|-------------------|----------------|----------|--------|\n147: | [path/to/file] | [D1, D3] | [N] | [0 P0, 1 P1, 2 P2] | [partial/complete] |\n148: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n149: \n150: ---\n151: \n152: ## 16. REVIEW BOUNDARIES\n153: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n154: - Max iterations: [from config]\n155: - Convergence threshold: [from config]\n156: - Rolling STOP threshold: 0.08\n157: - No-progress threshold: 0.05\n158: - Coverage stabilization passes required: 1\n159: - Session lineage: sessionId=[from config.sessionId], parentSessionId=[from config.parentSessionId], generation=[from config.generation], lineageMode=[from config.lineageMode]\n160: - Findings registry: `deep-review-findings-registry.json`\n161: - Release-readiness states: in-progress | converged | release-blocking\n162: - Per-iteration budget: [from config.maxToolCallsPerIteration] tool calls, [from config.maxMinutesPerIteration] minutes\n163: - Severity threshold: [from config.severityThreshold]\n164: - Review target type: [from config.reviewTargetType]\n165: - Cross-reference checks: core=[from config.crossReference.core], overlay=[from config.crossReference.overlay]\n166: - Started: [timestamp]\n167: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n168: \n169: ---\n170: \n171: ## 17. EXAMPLE (POPULATED)\n172: \n173: Reference snippet showing a partially populated strategy file mid-review. Use this as a visual anchor when opening a live strategy doc.\n174: \n175: ```markdown\n176: ## 1. REVIEW CHARTER\n177: - Target: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research (skill, v1.4.0)\n178: - Dimensions: correctness, test-coverage, cross-runtime-parity, observability\n179: - Stop conditions: rolling newInfoRatio < 0.08 for 2 iterations OR all dimensions converged OR max=7 reached\n180: - Success criteria: zero P0 in correctness; test-coverage P0 resolved or deferred with rationale\n181: \n182: ## 4. NEXT FOCUS\n183: - Dimension: test-coverage\n184: - Files: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs, .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/tests/deep-research-contract-parity.vitest.ts\n185: - Why: Iteration 2 surfaced a P0 (convergence-path coverage gap); needs a focused follow-up before correctness can terminate PASS.\n186: \n187: ## 9. COVERAGE MATRIX\n188: | Dimension            | Status     | Iterations touched |\n189: |----------------------|------------|--------------------|\n190: | correctness          | converged  | 1                  |\n191: | test-coverage        | converging | 2, 4               |\n192: | cross-runtime-parity | converging | 3                  |\n193: | observability        | converging | 4                  |\n194: ```\n\n(End of file - total 194 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Review Strategy Template\ndescription: Runtime template copied to review/ during initialization to track review progress, dimension coverage, findings, and outcomes across iterations.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review strategy template\"\n  - \"review dimension tracking\"\n  - \"exhausted review approaches\"\n  - \"review session tracking\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: planning\n---\n\n# Deep Review Strategy - Session Tracking Template\n\nRuntime template copied into the resolved `{artifact_dir}/` during initialization. Tracks review progress across iterations.\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_strategy.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Review Strategy Template\ndescription: Runtime template copied to review/ during initialization to track review progress, dimension coverage, findings, and outcomes across iterations.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review strategy template\"\n  - \"review dimension tracking\"\n  - \"exhausted review approaches\"\n  - \"review session tracking\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: planning\n---\n\n# Deep Review Strategy - Session Tracking Template\n\nRuntime template copied into the resolved `{artifact_dir}/` during initialization. Tracks review progress across iterations.\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nServes as the \"persistent brain\" for a deep review session. Records which dimensions remain, what was found (P0/P1/P2), what review approaches worked or failed, and where to focus next. Read by the orchestrator and agents at every iteration.\n\n### Usage\n\n- **Init:** Orchestrator copies this template to `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md` and populates Topic, Review Dimensions, Known Context, and Review Boundaries from config and memory context.\n- **Per iteration:** Agent reads Next Focus, reviews the assigned dimension/files, updates findings, marks dimensions complete, and sets new Next Focus.\n- **Mutability:** Mutable, updated by both orchestrator and agents throughout the session.\n- **Protection:** None (shared mutable state). Orchestrator validates consistency on resume.\n- **Ownership:** Machine-managed metrics and coverage blocks are wrapped in explicit ownership markers. Human commentary and operator overrides live outside those markers.\n\n---\n\n## 2. TOPIC\n[Review target description from config -- set during initialization]\n\n---\n\n## 3. REVIEW DIMENSIONS (remaining)\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n- [ ] D1 Correctness, Logic errors, off-by-one, wrong return types, broken invariants\n- [ ] D2 Security, Injection, auth bypass, secrets exposure, unsafe deserialization\n- [ ] D3 Traceability, Spec/code alignment, checklist evidence, cross-reference integrity\n- [ ] D4 Maintainability, Patterns, clarity, documentation quality, safe follow-on change cost\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 4. NON-GOALS\n[What this review session is NOT trying to assess -- populated during initialization]\n\n---\n\n## 5. STOP CONDITIONS\n[Explicit conditions beyond convergence that should end the session -- populated during initialization]\n\n---\n\n## 6. COMPLETED DIMENSIONS\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n[None yet -- populated as iterations complete dimension reviews]\n\n| Dimension | Verdict | Iteration | Summary |\n|-----------|---------|-----------|---------|\n| [D1 Correctness] | [PASS/CONDITIONAL/FAIL] | [N] | [1-sentence result] |\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 7. RUNNING FINDINGS\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n- **P0 (Critical):** 0 active\n- **P1 (Major):** 0 active\n- **P2 (Minor):** 0 active\n- **Delta this iteration:** +0 P0, +0 P1, +0 P2\n\n[Findings are tracked in `deep-review-findings-registry.json`. This section provides a running count summary updated after each iteration.]\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 8. WHAT WORKED\n[First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n- [Approach]: [Why it worked] (iteration N)\n\n---\n\n## 9. WHAT FAILED\n[First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n- [Approach]: [Why it failed] (iteration N)\n\n---\n\n## 10. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n[Populated when a review approach has been tried from multiple angles without yielding new findings]\n\n### [Category Name] -- BLOCKED (iteration N, N attempts)\n- What was tried: [specific review approaches attempted]\n- Why blocked: [root cause of exhaustion]\n- Do NOT retry: [explicit prohibition]\n\n### [Category Name] -- PRODUCTIVE (iteration N)\n- What worked: [successful review approaches in this category]\n- Prefer for: [related dimensions where this category may help]\n\n---\n\n## 11. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n[Review angles that were investigated and definitively eliminated -- consolidated from iteration dead-end data]\n- [Approach]: [Why ruled out] (iteration N, evidence: [source])\n\n---\n\n## 12. NEXT FOCUS\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n[Recommended focus area for the next iteration -- updated at end of each iteration. Includes target dimension and/or specific files to review.]\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 13. KNOWN CONTEXT\n[Populated during initialization from memory_context() results, if any prior work exists]\n\n---\n\n## 14. CROSS-REFERENCE STATUS\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n[Alignment checks completed across core and overlay protocols]\n\n| Protocol | Level | Status | Iteration | Notes |\n|----------|-------|--------|-----------|-------|\n| `spec_code` | core | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked] | [N] | [details] |\n| `checklist_evidence` | core | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked] | [N] | [details] |\n| `skill_agent` | overlay | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked/notApplicable] | [N] | [details] |\n| `agent_cross_runtime` | overlay | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked/notApplicable] | [N] | [details] |\n| `feature_catalog_code` | overlay | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked/notApplicable] | [N] | [details] |\n| `playbook_capability` | overlay | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked/notApplicable] | [N] | [details] |\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 15. FILES UNDER REVIEW\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n[Per-file coverage state table -- populated during initialization from scope discovery]\n\n| File | Dimensions Reviewed | Last Iteration | Findings | Status |\n|------|-------------------|----------------|----------|--------|\n| [path/to/file] | [D1, D3] | [N] | [0 P0, 1 P1, 2 P2] | [partial/complete] |\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 16. REVIEW BOUNDARIES\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n- Max iterations: [from config]\n- Convergence threshold: [from config]\n- Rolling STOP threshold: 0.08\n- No-progress threshold: 0.05\n- Coverage stabilization passes required: 1\n- Session lineage: sessionId=[from config.sessionId], parentSessionId=[from config.parentSessionId], generation=[from config.generation], lineageMode=[from config.lineageMode]\n- Findings registry: `deep-review-findings-registry.json`\n- Release-readiness states: in-progress | converged | release-blocking\n- Per-iteration budget: [from config.maxToolCallsPerIteration] tool calls, [from config.maxMinutesPerIteration] minutes\n- Severity threshold: [from config.severityThreshold]\n- Review target type: [from config.reviewTargetType]\n- Cross-reference checks: core=[from config.crossReference.core], overlay=[from config.crossReference.overlay]\n- Started: [timestamp]\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 17. EXAMPLE (POPULATED)\n\nReference snippet showing a partially populated strategy file mid-review. Use this as a visual anchor when opening a live strategy doc.\n\n```markdown\n## 1. REVIEW CHARTER\n- Target: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research (skill, v1.4.0)\n- Dimensions: correctness, test-coverage, cross-runtime-parity, observability\n- Stop conditions: rolling newInfoRatio < 0.08 for 2 iterations OR all dimensions converged OR max=7 reached\n- Success criteria: zero P0 in correctness; test-coverage P0 resolved or deferred with rationale\n\n## 4. NEXT FOCUS\n- Dimension: test-coverage\n- Files: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs, .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/tests/deep-research-contract-parity.vitest.ts\n- Why: Iteration 2 surfaced a P0 (convergence-path coverage gap); needs a focused follow-up before correctness can terminate PASS.\n\n## 9. COVERAGE MATRIX\n| Dimension            | Status     | Iterations touched |\n|----------------------|------------|--------------------|\n| correctness          | converged  | 1                  |\n| test-coverage        | converging | 2, 4               |\n| cross-runtime-parity | converging | 3                  |\n| observability        | converging | 4                  |\n```","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":194,"totalLines":194,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_strategy.md","time":{"start":1781756713939,"end":1781756713942}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0606ee1f4d679b5d016a337329d6248191a034e6b553708a14"}},"id":"prt_ed8f9dbd2001jLjdekiy3dYZGP","sessionID":"ses_1270761dbffecw7Dfym5Wp50VJ","messageID":"msg_ed8f9ac4b0015LFGMJKspDbNZp"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781756713946,"sessionID":"ses_1270761dbffecw7Dfym5Wp50VJ","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_2Ywzn6ow7IyUa4wUHhjX8qVk","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml","offset":1,"limit":500},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n2: # DEEP REVIEW: AUTONOMOUS DEEP REVIEW LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n3: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n4: # DEEP REVIEW: AUTONOMOUS DEEP REVIEW LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n5: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n6: role: Deep Review Loop Manager\n7: purpose: Iterative code/spec review with convergence detection across review dimensions\n8: action: Run deep-review loop from initialization through synthesis\n9: operating_mode:\n10:   workflow: iterative_loop\n11:   workflow_compliance: MANDATORY\n12:   workflow_execution: autonomous\n13:   approvals: none\n14:   tracking: progressive_review_state\n15:   validation: convergence_detection\n16: \n17: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n18: # OPERATING PRINCIPLES\n19: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n20: operating_principles:\n21:   core: \"Fresh context per iteration + externalized state = no context degradation\"\n22:   approach: \"Dispatch focused review agent per dimension, evaluate convergence, repeat or stop\"\n23:   mandate: \"Never hold findings in memory; write everything to files. Review target is READ-ONLY.\"\n24: \n25: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n26: # USER INPUTS (from setup phase)\n27: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n28: user_inputs:\n29:   review_target: \"[REVIEW_TARGET] - What to review. REQUIRED.\"\n30:   review_target_type: \"[spec-folder|skill|agent|track|files] - Target type for scope derivation. REQUIRED.\"\n31:   review_dimensions: \"[all|correctness,security,traceability,maintainability] - Dimensions to check. Default: all.\"\n32:   spec_folder: \"[SPEC_FOLDER] - Spec folder path for state files. REQUIRED.\"\n33:   lineage_mode: \"[auto|resume|restart] - Session lifecycle intent. Default: auto. The runtime only persists lineage events for `resume` (same sessionId, no archive) and `restart` (new sessionId, generation+1, prior review/ archived). `fork` and `completed-continue` are deferred and no longer accepted — see deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md §Lifecycle Branches.\"\n34:   max_iterations: 7\n35:   convergence_threshold: 0.10\n36: \n37: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n38: # CONTEXT LOADING\n39: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n40: context_loading:\n41:   trigger: \"At workflow START, before phase_init\"\n42:   purpose: \"Load prior review context for the target and buffer it until strategy.md exists\"\n43:   mcp_integration:\n44:     tool: memory_context\n45:     note: \"Call MCP tools directly - NEVER through Code Mode\"\n46:     parameters: { input: \"{review_target}\", mode: \"focused\", intent: \"understand\", includeContent: true }\n47:   when_to_skip: [\"User says 'skip context' or 'fresh start'\"]\n48:   behavior:\n49:     if_context_found: \"Store full results as prior_context plus a concise prior_context_summary; inject after strategy.md is created.\"\n50:     if_no_context: \"Set prior_context and prior_context_summary to 'None' and continue.\"\n51: \n52: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n53: # SKILL REFERENCE\n54: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n55: skill_reference:\n56:   skill: deep-loop-workflows\n57:   skill_md: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/SKILL.md\n58:   references:\n59:     loop_protocol: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\n60:     state_format: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/state/state_format.md\n61:     convergence: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/convergence/convergence.md\n62:   templates:\n63:     config: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_config.json\n64:     strategy: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_strategy.md\n65: \n66: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n67: # AGENT CONFIGURATION\n68: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n69: agent_config:\n70:   agent: deep-review\n71:   agent_file: \".opencode/agents/deep-review.md\"\n72:   # Canonical path. Runtime-specific directories (e.g. .claude/agents/) reference this source.\n73:   mode: subagent\n74:   model: opus\n75:   leaf_only: true\n76:   tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob]\n77:   mcp_servers: [mk-spec-memory]\n78:   tool_call_budget: { target: 9, soft_max: 12, hard_max: 13 }\n79: \n80: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n81: # STATE FILE PATHS\n82: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n83: state_paths:\n84:   # Template paths document the canonical packet layout. Runtime resolution happens via\n85:   # step_resolve_artifact_root plus the shared resolver, so root specs keep\n86:   # root-local review/ and child phases keep local review/ packet dirs.\n87:   # Canonical root-spec write targets remain review/deep-review-config.json,\n88:   # review/deep-review-state.jsonl, and review/deep-review-findings-registry.json.\n89:   packet_dir: \"{artifact_dir}\"\n90:   local_packet_dir: \"{spec_folder}/review\"\n91:   legacy_root_report: \"{spec_folder}/review-report.md\"\n92:   config: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-config.json\"\n93:   state_log: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-state.jsonl\"\n94:   findings_registry: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-findings-registry.json\"\n95:   strategy: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md\"\n96:   dashboard: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-dashboard.md\"\n97:   pause_sentinel: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-review-pause\"\n98:   lock_file: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-review.lock\"\n99:   prompt_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/prompts\"\n100:   iteration_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations\"\n101:   iteration_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md\"\n102:   # Per-iteration structured delta stream — complement to the canonical state_log\n103:   # append. MUST contain at least one record with `type === \"iteration\"`; variants\n104:   # like `\"iteration_delta\"` are silently dropped by the reducer.\n105:   delta_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas\"\n106:   delta_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas/iter-{NNN}.jsonl\"\n107:   review_output: \"{artifact_dir}/review-report.md\"\n108:   resource_map_output: \"{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md\"\n109:   archive_root: \"{artifact_archive_root}\"\n110: \n111: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n112: # WORKFLOW\n113: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n114: workflow:\n115: \n116:   step_resolve_artifact_root:\n117:     description: \"Resolve artifact directory — use fan-out lineage override when provided, else resolve from spec_folder\"\n118:     note: \"Root specs keep review artifacts directly in {spec_folder}/review/. Child phases and sub-phases keep local packet directories in {spec_folder}/review/{packet}/, and archives stay local at {spec_folder}/review_archive/{packet}/.\"\n119:     branch_on: \"config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir\"\n120:     if_present:\n121:       bind:\n122:         artifact_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n123:         artifact_root_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n124:         artifact_subfolder: null\n125:         artifact_archive_root: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}/_archive\"\n126:     if_absent:\n127:       command: \"node -e \\\"const { resolveArtifactRoot } = require('.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs'); console.log(JSON.stringify(resolveArtifactRoot('{spec_folder}', 'review')));\\\"\"\n128:       outputs:\n129:         - artifact_root_dir: \"Resolved local review owner directory\"\n130:         - artifact_subfolder: \"Local packet subfolder ({ownerSlug}-pt-{NN}), else null\"\n131:         - artifact_dir: \"Resolved review packet directory for this target\"\n132:         - artifact_archive_root: \"Resolved local review archive directory for this target\"\n133: \n134:   step_fanout_spawn:\n135:     description: \"Spawn fan-out lineages; skip and proceed to phase_init normally when single-executor\"\n136:     skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"\n137:     instructions: |\n138:       Fan-out mode is active. Spawn all lineages. Each lineage runs the full loop in its own\n139:       isolated sub-packet under {artifact_dir}/lineages/{label}/.\n140:       After all lineages complete, jump directly to phase_synthesis — skip phase_init and\n141:       phase_main_loop entirely (those are the single-executor path). The merge step in\n142:       phase_synthesis will consolidate results across all lineages.\n143:     sub_steps:\n144:       step_fanout_spawn_cli:\n145:         description: \"Spawn all CLI lineages in capped worker pool\"\n146:         skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors with kind != 'native'\"\n147:         command: |\n148:           node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs \\\n149:             --spec-folder {spec_folder} \\\n150:             --loop-type review \\\n151:             --fanout-config-json '{config.fanout_json}' \\\n152:             --base-artifact-dir {artifact_dir}\n153:         working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n154:         wait_for_completion: true\n155:       step_fanout_spawn_native:\n156:         description: \"Dispatch each native lineage as a sequential deep-review sub-agent\"\n157:         skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors with kind == 'native'\"\n158:         for_each: \"lineage in expanded native entries of config.fanout\"\n159:         dispatch:\n160:           agent: deep-review\n161:           model: opus\n162:           context: |\n163:             Execute the deep-review loop with these parameters:\n164:               spec_folder: {spec_folder}\n165:               config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir: {artifact_dir}/lineages/{lineage.label}\n166:               session_id: fanout-{lineage.label}-{fanout_run_id}\n167:               executor: native\n168:             Run to convergence. Write all outputs to the override directory.\n169:         wait_for_completion: true\n170: \n171:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n172:   # PHASE 1: INITIALIZATION\n173:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n174:   phase_init:\n175:     purpose: Create all state files for the review session and resolve review scope\n176:     steps:\n177: \n178:       step_preflight_contract:\n179:         action: \"Validate required setup bindings and executable workflow contract before any file writes\"\n180:         verify:\n181:           - required_values_present: [review_target, review_target_type, review_dimensions, spec_folder, max_iterations, convergence_threshold]\n182:           - spec_folder_is_within: \"specs/ or .opencode/specs/ (canonicalize alias roots before validation)\"\n183:           - unresolved_placeholders: \"FAIL if any user-facing template references placeholders not produced by earlier steps\"\n184:           - tool_contract: \"FAIL if executable steps reference tools outside the command allowlist\"\n185:         on_fail: \"Halt with STATUS=FAIL and report the missing binding or unsupported contract reference\"\n186: \n187:       step_create_directories:\n188:         action: \"Create spec folder and canonical review packet directories if they don't exist\"\n189:         command: \"mkdir -p {state_paths.prompt_dir} {state_paths.iteration_dir} {state_paths.delta_dir}\"\n190: \n191:       step_detect_resource_map:\n192:         action: \"Detect resource-map.md before config creation so init can persist coverage-gate state\"\n193:         inspect:\n194:           - \"{spec_folder}/resource-map.md\"\n195:         classify:\n196:           present: \"resource-map.md exists at init\"\n197:           absent: \"resource-map.md does not exist at init\"\n198:         outputs:\n199:           - resource_map_present: \"Boolean true when {spec_folder}/resource-map.md exists, else false\"\n200:           - resource_map_known_context: \"When present: concise resource-map snapshot for Known Context and charter framing. When absent: 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n201: \n202:       step_migrate_legacy_review_state:\n203:         action: \"Rehome legacy review artifacts into review/iterations before session classification\"\n204:         detect:\n205:           canonical_review_state:\n206:             - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n207:             - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n208:             - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n209:             - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n210:           legacy_review_state:\n211:             - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json\"\n212:             - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl\"\n213:             - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md\"\n214:             - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-dashboard.md\"\n215:             - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/iteration-*.md\"\n216:             - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/.deep-research-pause\"\n217:             - \"{state_paths.local_packet_dir}/iteration-*.md\"\n218:             - \"{state_paths.legacy_root_report}\"\n219:           legacy_review_markers:\n220:             - \"scratch/deep-review-strategy.md exists\"\n221:             - \"scratch/deep-research-config.json declares mode == 'review' OR scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl contains mode == 'review'\"\n222:         migrate_only:\n223:           - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json -> {state_paths.config}\"\n224:           - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl -> {state_paths.state_log}\"\n225:           - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md -> {state_paths.strategy}\"\n226:           - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-dashboard.md -> {state_paths.dashboard}\"\n227:           - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/iteration-*.md -> {state_paths.iteration_dir}/\"\n228:           - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/.deep-research-pause -> {state_paths.pause_sentinel}\"\n229:           - \"{state_paths.local_packet_dir}/iteration-*.md -> {state_paths.iteration_dir}/\"\n230:           - \"{state_paths.legacy_root_report} -> {state_paths.review_output}\"\n231:         on_canonical_present: \"Leave canonical review/ state untouched and do not overwrite it with legacy scratch artifacts.\"\n232:         on_legacy_detected: \"Move only the review-specific whitelist, append a migration event to the canonical JSONL, and leave unrelated scratch files untouched.\"\n233:         on_conflict: \"If canonical review/ state and legacy scratch review state both exist but disagree, halt for operator repair instead of merging contradictory state.\"\n234:         command: \"mkdir -p {state_paths.iteration_dir} && if [ ! -e {state_paths.config} ] && [ ! -e {state_paths.state_log} ] && [ ! -e {state_paths.strategy} ] && [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md ] && ( [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json ] || [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl ] ); then [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json {state_paths.config}; [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl {state_paths.state_log}; [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md {state_paths.strategy}; [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-dashboard.md ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-dashboard.md {state_paths.dashboard}; find {spec_folder}/scratch -maxdepth 1 -name 'iteration-*.md' -exec mv {} {state_paths.iteration_dir}/ \\\\; ; [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/.deep-research-pause ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/.deep-research-pause {state_paths.pause_sentinel}; [ -e {state_paths.legacy_root_report} ] && mv {state_paths.legacy_root_report} {state_paths.review_output}; if [ -e {state_paths.state_log} ]; then printf '%s\\n' '{\\\"type\\\":\\\"event\\\",\\\"event\\\":\\\"migration\\\",\\\"mode\\\":\\\"review\\\",\\\"legacyArtifacts\\\":[\\\"deep-research-config.json\\\",\\\"deep-research-state.jsonl\\\",\\\".deep-research-pause\\\"],\\\"canonicalArtifacts\\\":[\\\"deep-review-config.json\\\",\\\"deep-review-state.jsonl\\\",\\\".deep-review-pause\\\"],\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\\\"}' >> {state_paths.state_log}; fi; fi; find {state_paths.local_packet_dir} -maxdepth 1 -name 'iteration-*.md' -exec mv {} {state_paths.iteration_dir}/ \\\\; 2>/dev/null || true\"\n235: \n236:       step_acquire_lock:\n237:         action: \"Acquire the single-writer advisory lock before session classification\"\n238:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs acquire --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --packet-id {spec_folder}\"\n239:         on_acquire: \"Capture ownerPid from the JSON output and reuse it for every release below. If acquired=false, fail closed — another deep-review run already holds this packet.\"\n240:         note: \"Uses the promoted deep-loop-runtime loop-lock CLI (single source of truth: stale-lock reclaim, clean owner-scoped release). macOS/BSD locking is advisory — best-effort single-writer, not a hard mutex across host calls; stale-lock override is confirm-only or explicit recovery-only.\"\n241:         # Lock-cleanup contract: the lock file MUST be released on every terminal exit path that follows acquisition.\n242:         # Runtimes honoring step_acquire_lock are required to perform this cleanup before halting or pausing.\n243:         on_halt:\n244:           action: \"Release the lock before any terminal halt branch returns control\"\n245:           applies_to: [\"step_classify_session.on_invalid_state\", \"step_classify_session.on_completed_session\"]\n246:           command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; failures here are logged but do not block the halt\"\n247:         on_cancel:\n248:           action: \"Release the lock on user cancel or pause-sentinel detection before sentinel processing\"\n249:           command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; cancel completes regardless of cleanup result\"\n250:         on_workflow_exit:\n251:           action: \"Release the lock as the final step of any workflow exit path (success or failure)\"\n252:           command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; idempotent — safe to invoke when already released\"\n253: \n254:       step_classify_session:\n255:         action: \"Classify the session before writing files\"\n256:         inspect:\n257:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n258:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n259:           - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n260:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n261:         classify:\n262:           fresh: \"None of the three state artifacts exist\"\n263:           resume: \"Config, JSONL, and strategy all exist and config.mode == 'review' and agree on target/spec folder\"\n264:           completed-session: \"Resume artifacts exist and config.status == 'complete'\"\n265:           invalid-state: \"Any partial, missing, or contradictory combination\"\n266:         outputs:\n267:           - session_state: \"fresh | resume | completed-session | invalid-state\"\n268:         on_resume:\n269:           log: \"Auto-resume: state artifacts are complete and consistent. Continue the same lineage (sessionId unchanged, generation unchanged, no archive).\"\n270:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"resume\",\"continuedFromRun\":{iteration_count},\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":null,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n271:           skip_to: phase_loop\n272:         on_restart:\n273:           action: \"Archive the current review packet under the root-level review_archive/ tree and start a new lineage segment with a fresh sessionId and generation+1.\"\n274:           command: \"if [ -d {state_paths.packet_dir} ]; then mkdir -p {state_paths.archive_root} && mv {state_paths.packet_dir} {state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}; fi\"\n275:           set:\n276:             lineage_mode: \"restart\"\n277:             parent_session_id: \"{prior_session_id}\"\n278:             generation: \"{prior_generation + 1}\"\n279:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"restarted\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{prior_session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"restart\",\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":\"{state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n280:           skip_to: step_create_config\n281:         note_deferred_branches: \"fork and completed-continue are deferred and no longer runtime-supported in this release. The reducer still reads `lineageMode` from config for dashboards and analysis, but only `new`, `resume`, and `restart` are live. See deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md §Lifecycle Branches for the one-session contract.\"\n282:         on_completed_session:\n283:           log: \"Prior session already completed. Either archive the completed review/ tree and start a fresh session, or jump straight to synthesis with the existing artifacts.\"\n284:           skip_to: phase_synthesis\n285:         on_invalid_state:\n286:           halt: true\n287:           message: \"Existing deep-review state in review/ is incomplete or contradictory. Repair or archive the invalid review packet before continuing.\"\n288:         on_fresh:\n289:           action: \"Proceed with a new session\"\n290: \n291:       step_scope_discovery:\n292:         action: \"Resolve review target to a concrete file list based on target type\"\n293:         resolve:\n294:           spec-folder: |\n295:             1. Read spec.md, plan.md, tasks.md, checklist.md, implementation-summary.md\n296:             2. Discover implementation files referenced in spec artifacts\n297:             3. Discover test files associated with implementation\n298:             4. Set scope = all discovered files\n299:           skill: |\n300:             1. Read SKILL.md from .opencode/skills/{skill_name}/\n301:             2. Discover references/, assets/, scripts/ contents\n302:             3. Find agent definitions referencing this skill across runtimes\n303:             4. Find command entry points referencing this skill\n304:             5. Set scope = all discovered files\n305:           agent: |\n306:             1. Find agent definition across repo-managed runtimes (.claude/agents/, .opencode/agents/, .codex/agents/, .agents/)\n307:             2. Compare agent definitions for consistency\n308:             3. Set scope = all discovered agent files\n309:           track: |\n310:             1. List all child spec folders under specs/{track}/ or .opencode/specs/{track}/\n311:             2. For each: read spec.md + checklist.md\n312:             3. Set scope = all child spec artifacts\n313:           files: |\n314:             1. Expand glob patterns from review_target\n315:             2. Validate all files exist\n316:             3. Discover immediate cross-references (imports, links)\n317:             4. Set scope = expanded file list + cross-references\n318:         outputs:\n319:           - review_scope_files: \"List of all files in review scope\"\n320:           - cross_reference_targets: \"{ spec_paths: [...], code_paths: [...], test_paths: [...] }\"\n321: \n322:       step_order_dimensions:\n323:         action: \"Order review dimensions based on risk priority\"\n324:         algorithm: |\n325:           1. Iteration 0 (inventory pass): Build artifact map, identify file types, estimate complexity\n326:           2. Subsequent iterations follow risk-ordered deep passes:\n327:              correctness → security → traceability → maintainability\n328:           3. If review_dimensions != \"all\", filter to only requested dimensions\n329:           4. Derive traceability protocol plan:\n330:              - core: spec_code, checklist_evidence\n331:              - overlay: skill_agent, agent_cross_runtime, feature_catalog_code, playbook_capability\n332:           5. If resource_map_present, reserve at least one traceability-oriented pass to cross-check target_files from applied/T-*.md against resource-map.md and classify touched / expected-by-scope / gap / absent-from-map outcomes\n333:           6. Store ordered list as dimension_queue\n334:         outputs:\n335:           - dimension_queue: \"Ordered list of dimensions to review\"\n336:           - inventory_pass: true\n337: \n338:       step_normalize_review_dimensions:\n339:         action: \"Normalize reviewDimensions once during init for config + JSONL reuse\"\n340:         outputs:\n341:           - review_dimensions_normalized: \"Canonical string[] for deep-review-config.json\"\n342:           - review_dimensions_json: \"JSON.stringify(review_dimensions_normalized) for JSONL config record\"\n343:         normalize: |\n344:           Accept {review_dimensions} in any of these shapes and convert once:\n345:             - \"all\" → [\"correctness\",\"security\",\"traceability\",\"maintainability\"]\n346:             - \"correctness,security\" → [\"correctness\",\"security\"]\n347:             - [\"correctness\"] → [\"correctness\"]\n348:           Every element MUST be one of the four canonical dimension names.\n349: \n350:       step_create_config:\n351:         action: \"Create deep-review-config.json from template with review-specific fields\"\n352:         template: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_config.json\n353:         populate:\n354:           topic: \"Review: {review_target}\"\n355:           mode: \"review\"\n356:           sessionId: \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"\n357:           parentSessionId: null\n358:           lineageMode: \"new\"\n359:           generation: 1\n360:           continuedFromRun: null\n361:           reviewTarget: \"{review_target}\"\n362:           reviewTargetType: \"{review_target_type}\"\n363:           # Reuse the single normalized init-time value from step_normalize_review_dimensions.\n364:           reviewDimensions: \"{review_dimensions_normalized}\"\n365:           resource_map_present: \"{resource_map_present}\"\n366:           reviewScopeFiles: \"{review_scope_files}\"\n367:           severityThreshold: \"P2\"\n368:           crossReference:\n369:             core: [\"spec_code\", \"checklist_evidence\"]\n370:             overlay: [\"skill_agent\", \"agent_cross_runtime\", \"feature_catalog_code\", \"playbook_capability\"]\n371:           maxIterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n372:           # Semantic: weighted P0/P1/P2 severity ratio. See SKILL.md §\"Convergence Threshold Semantics\".\n373:           convergenceThreshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n374:           stuckThreshold: 2\n375:           maxDurationMinutes: 120\n376:           specFolder: \"{spec_folder}\"\n377:           # <!-- F-010-B5-04 -->\n378:           # Honor the parsed --no-resource-map flag from deep-review.md:71 (default true; false when flag is set).\n379:           # The markdown command parses $ARGUMENTS and binds {resource_map_emit} before this step runs.\n380:           resource_map.emit: \"{resource_map_emit}\"\n381:           createdAt: \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"\n382:           status: \"initialized\"\n383:           releaseReadinessState: \"in-progress\"\n384:           executionMode: \"auto\"\n385:         output: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n386: \n387:       step_create_state_log:\n388:         action: \"Initialize JSONL state log with config record including review fields and lineage metadata\"\n389:         note: \"Reuse review_dimensions_json from step_normalize_review_dimensions. Never re-normalize or wrap the raw template value.\"\n390:         # <!-- F-010-B5-04 -->\n391:         # Same parsed --no-resource-map flag honored here so config and state_log agree from line 1.\n392:         content: '{\"type\":\"config\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"reviewTarget\":\"{review_target}\",\"reviewTargetType\":\"{review_target_type}\",\"reviewDimensions\":{review_dimensions_json},\"resource_map_present\":{resource_map_present},\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":{resource_map_emit}},\"sessionId\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"parentSessionId\":null,\"lineageMode\":\"new\",\"generation\":1,\"continuedFromRun\":null,\"maxIterations\":{max_iterations},\"convergenceThreshold\":{convergence_threshold},\"createdAt\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"specFolder\":\"{spec_folder}\"}'\n393:         output: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n394: \n395:       step_create_findings_registry:\n396:         action: \"Initialize reducer-owned review findings registry\"\n397:         content: '{\"sessionId\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"generation\":1,\"lineageMode\":\"new\",\"openFindings\":[],\"resolvedFindings\":[],\"repeatedFindings\":[],\"dimensionCoverage\":{\"correctness\":false,\"security\":false,\"traceability\":false,\"maintainability\":false},\"findingsBySeverity\":{\"P0\":0,\"P1\":0,\"P2\":0},\"openFindingsCount\":0,\"resolvedFindingsCount\":0,\"convergenceScore\":0.0}'\n398:         output: \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n399: \n400:       step_create_strategy:\n401:         action: \"Create review strategy file from deep_review_strategy.md template\"\n402:         template: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_strategy.md\n403:         populate:\n404:           review_target: \"{review_target}\"\n405:           review_target_type: \"{review_target_type}\"\n406:           dimensions: \"{dimension_queue}\"\n407:           scope_files: \"{review_scope_files}\"\n408:           cross_reference_targets: \"{cross_reference_targets}\"\n409:           max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n410:           convergence_threshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n411:         output: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n412: \n413:       step_enrich_strategy_context:\n414:         action: \"Ensure Known Context is written only after strategy.md exists\"\n415:         condition: \"prior_context_found\"\n416:         edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n417:         note: \"Append or replace the Known Context section with prior_context_summary and retained detail from prior_context\"\n418: \n419:       step_enrich_strategy_resource_map:\n420:         action: \"Inject resource-map status into Known Context after strategy.md exists\"\n421:         edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n422:         note: \"When resource_map_present is true, append the resource_map_known_context snapshot and add Resource Map Coverage to the Review Charter. When false, append 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n423: \n424:       step_init_complete:\n425:         log: \"Initialization complete. Config, state, and strategy files created. Review scope: {review_scope_files_count} files, {dimension_queue_count} dimensions.\"\n426:         set: { current_iteration: 1, stuck_count: 0, p0_count: 0, p1_count: 0, p2_count: 0 }\n427: \n428:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n429:   # PHASE 2: ITERATION LOOP\n430:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n431:   phase_loop:\n432:     purpose: Dispatch review agent iterations until convergence\n433:     repeat: true\n434:     max_repeats: \"{max_iterations}\"\n435:     steps:\n436: \n437:       step_read_state:\n438:         action: \"Read current state from JSONL, strategy, and config\"\n439:         read:\n440:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n441:           - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n442:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n443:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n444:         extract:\n445:           - iteration_count: \"Count lines where type === 'iteration'\"\n446:           - current_iteration: \"iteration_count + 1\"\n447:           - last_newFindingsRatio: \"Extract newFindingsRatio from last iteration record\"\n448:           - last_focus: \"Extract focus/dimension from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n449:           - ratio_prev: \"Extract newFindingsRatio from second-latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n450:           - ratio_latest: \"Extract newFindingsRatio from latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n451:           - next_dimension: \"Next uncovered dimension from dimension_queue in strategy.md\"\n452:           - dimensions_covered: \"List of dimensions already reviewed\"\n453:           - dimensions_remaining: \"List of dimensions not yet reviewed\"\n454:           - dimension_coverage: \"covered / total dimensions\"\n455:           - coverage_age: \"Iterations since dimension coverage last changed; require >= 1 before STOP\"\n456:           - p0_count: \"Count P0 findings across all iterations\"\n457:           - p1_count: \"Count P1 findings across all iterations\"\n458:           - p2_count: \"Count P2 findings across all iterations\"\n459:           - resource_map_present: \"Extract boolean from deep-review-config.json, default false\"\n460:           - resource_map_prompt_line: \"If resource_map_present is true, return 'Resource Map Coverage: cross-check target_files from {spec_folder}/applied/T-*.md against {spec_folder}/resource-map.md and classify only missed coverage as gaps.' Else return 'Resource Map Coverage: resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate.'\"\n461:           - session_id: \"Extract sessionId from deep-review-config.json\"\n462:           - generation: \"Extract generation from deep-review-config.json, else 1\"\n463:           - last_3_summaries: \"Summarize the latest 3 iteration records as 'run N: dimension (ratio, P0/P1/P2)'\"\n464:           - latest_status: \"Extract status from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n465:           - last_claim_adjudication_passed: \"Scan state.jsonl for the most recent `claim_adjudication` event; use its `passed` boolean. Default true when no event exists or when activeP0 + activeP1 == 0 (gate is vacuous without adjudicable findings).\"\n466:           - claim_adjudication_active_count: \"Count of active P0/P1 findings at the time of the last claim_adjudication event; 0 when none exist\"\n467:           - security_sensitive_fix_scope: \"Boolean true when the current review is a rerun after fixes involving security, path disclosure, auth/authz, sandboxing, env precedence, public schemas, persistence, or user-visible error payloads; derive from the latest review report, remediation notes, or planning packet when present, else false.\"\n468:           - fix_completeness_replay_required_rows: \"Count prior active or remediated P0/P1 findings, plus any prior security/path P2 findings, that require closed-gate replay before STOP.\"\n469:           - fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows: \"Count required replay rows marked PASS with file:line or command evidence and producer/consumer/matrix coverage.\"\n470: \n471:       step_check_pause_sentinel:\n472:         action: \"Check for pause sentinel file\"\n473:         check: \"Does {state_paths.pause_sentinel} exist?\"\n474:         if_exists:\n475:           set:\n476:             pending_stop_event: \"paused\"\n477:             pending_stop_reason: \"userPaused\"\n478:             pending_stop_detail: \"sentinel file detected\"\n479:           skip_to: step_normalize_pause_events\n480:         if_not_exists:\n481:           proceed: true\n482: \n483:       step_graph_convergence:\n484:         action: \"Evaluate coverage-graph convergence before the inline review convergence vote\"\n485:         inspect:\n486:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n487:           - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n488:         transform: |\n489:           1. Call graph convergence on the current review lineage before the inline 3-signal vote.\n490:           2. Record the decision as one of CONTINUE, STOP_ALLOWED, STOP_BLOCKED.\n491:           3. Preserve raw graph signals and blockers for reducer rollup and blocked-stop evidence.\n492:           4. Normalize blockers to both JSON array and CSV forms for downstream stop handling.\n493:           5. Set graph_stop_blocked = true only when graph_decision == \"STOP_BLOCKED\".\n494:         bash: 'node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/convergence.cjs --spec-folder \"{spec_folder}\" --loop-type \"review\" --session-id \"{session_id}\"'\n495:         note: \"Invoke the runtime script directly. Review-side graph convergence must run before the inline review stop vote.\"\n496:         append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"graph_convergence\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"decision\":\"{graph_decision}\",\"signals\":{graph_signals_json},\"blockers\":{graph_blockers_json},\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n497:         outputs:\n498:           - graph_decision: \"CONTINUE | STOP_ALLOWED | STOP_BLOCKED\"\n499:           - graph_signals_json: \"JSON object returned by convergence.cjs\"\n500:           - graph_blockers_json: \"JSON array of graph blockers when present, else []\"\n\n(Showing lines 1-500 of 1441. Use offset=501 to continue.)\n</content>\n\n<system-reminder>\nInstructions from: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/CONTEXT.md\n---\ndescription: Codebase-context loop: heterogeneous parallel sweep with convergence detection. Modes :auto, :confirm.\nargument-hint: \"<scope> [:auto|:confirm] [--max-iterations=N] [--convergence=N] [--executor=<type> [--model=X] [--prompt-framework=X] [--label=X] ...] [--executors=<json>] [--concurrency=N] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\"\nallowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_query, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_context\n---\n\n# Deep Start Context Loop\n\nThin router for the deep-context loop. This command verifies the orchestrating agent, resolves setup and execution mode, loads the presentation contract, then executes the owned workflow YAML.\n\n## 1. ROUTER CONTRACT\n\nDo not dispatch agents from this Markdown file. Agent dispatch, workflow steps, and artifact-writing behavior are owned by the workflow YAML assets.\n\nLoad the presentation contract before showing startup questions, dashboards, checkpoints, success output, failure output, examples, or next-step prompts.\n\nThis command is **general-agent based** and must pass the @general verification gate before setup routing continues. Gate 1 (@general verification) and Gate 2 (the BLOCKED Unified Setup Phase) are HARD BLOCKS; neither may be skipped.\n\n### PHASE 0: @GENERAL AGENT VERIFICATION\n\n**STATUS: ☐ BLOCKED**\n\n```\nEXECUTE THIS AUTOMATIC SELF-CHECK (NOT A USER QUESTION):\n\nSELF-CHECK: Are you operating as the @general agent?\n│\n├─ INDICATORS that you ARE @general agent:\n│   ├─ You can orchestrate the deep-context loop (YAML workflow execution)\n│   ├─ You can orchestrate Read/Write/Edit/Bash workflow execution\n│   ├─ You can load skill references and execute defined logic\n│\n├─ IF YES (all indicators present):\n│   └─ general_agent_verified = TRUE → Continue to the Unified Setup Phase (also a HARD BLOCK)\n│\n└─ IF NO or UNCERTAIN:\n    │\n    ├─ ⛔ HARD BLOCK - DO NOT PROCEED\n    │\n    ├─ DISPLAY to user:\n    │   ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n    │   │ ⛔ GENERAL AGENT REQUIRED                                  │\n    │   │                                                            │\n    │   │ This command orchestrates the deep-context loop and runs   │\n    │   │ general-agent based.                                       │\n    │   │                                                            │\n    │   │ To proceed, restart with:                                  │\n    │   │   /deep:context [arguments]                                │ \n    │   └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n    │\n    └─ RETURN: STATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"General agent required\"\n```\n\n**Phase Output:**\n- `general_agent_verified = ________________`\n\n### MANDATORY INPUT GATE\n\n- **DO NOT** dispatch any agent from this document\n- **ALL** agent dispatching is handled by the YAML workflow steps\n- **MARKDOWN OWNS SETUP**: resolve setup inputs here first, then hand off to YAML\n- **YAML START CONDITION**: do not load YAML until ALL required inputs are bound:\n  - `scope`, `spec_folder`, `execution_mode`, `maxIterations`, `convergenceThreshold`\n- Resolve `executor_pool` before persisting config and entering the YAML workflow.\n\n---\n\n## 2. OWNED ASSETS\n\n| Purpose | Asset |\n|---------|-------|\n| Presentation source of truth | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_context_presentation.txt` |\n| Auto workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_context_auto.yaml` |\n| Confirm workflow | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_context_confirm.yaml` |\n\nNo workflow-asset gap exists for this command.\n\n---\n\n## 3. MODE ROUTING\n\n1. Parse `$ARGUMENTS` for attached command suffixes (`:auto` or `:confirm`). Canonical mode syntax is `/deep:context:auto` and `/deep:context:confirm`; keep AGENTS, skills, and quick references synchronized to this entrypoint.\n2. Treat scope text, `--max-iterations`, `--convergence`, relevance/agreement flags, executor pool flags, and pre-bound setup answers as workflow inputs, not execution modes.\n3. If `:auto` is present, set `execution_mode = AUTONOMOUS` and resolve required setup inputs through the presentation contract's three-tier auto setup resolution before loading YAML.\n4. If `:confirm` is present, set `execution_mode = INTERACTIVE` and use the presentation contract's consolidated setup prompt before loading YAML.\n5. If no mode suffix is present, set `execution_mode = ASK` and use the presentation contract's consolidated setup prompt to ask for execution mode.\n6. Load the selected workflow asset only after `scope`, `spec_folder`, `execution_mode`, `maxIterations`, `convergenceThreshold`, and `executor_pool` are bound.\n\n---\n\n## 4. EXECUTION TARGETS\n\n| Mode | Workflow |\n|------|----------|\n| `:auto` | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_context_auto.yaml` |\n| `:confirm` or interactive choice | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_context_confirm.yaml` |\n\n---\n\n## 5. PRESENTATION BOUNDARY\n\nThe following content lives only in `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_context_presentation.txt`:\n\n- Startup-question wording, consolidated setup prompt text, question text, and reply-format examples.\n- `:auto` pre-bound setup answer schema, default resolution table, targeted-ask rules, and fail-fast display behavior.\n- Dashboard/checkpoint layouts, workflow overview displays, convergence threshold semantics, runtime robustness/session classification displays, and memory/skill reference displays.\n- Success and failure result templates, output formats, and error-handling displays.\n- Example invocations, executor-pool explanation display, and next-step suggestion wording.\n\n---\n\n## 6. WORKFLOW SUMMARY\n\nThe YAML workflow runs iterative codebase-context gathering by seeding a `SLICE` frontier from the scope, dispatching every executor over the same focus as a parallel sweep, merging findings by `file:symbol` with agreement counts, and synthesizing a reuse-first Context Report under `context/`. Convergence uses deep-context's relevance-gated coverage saturation with agreement and relevance as blocking guards; do not transfer sibling defaults from deep-research or deep-review. Code graph tool IDs remain stable as `code_graph_query` and `code_graph_context`; implementation and docs live under `.opencode/skills/system-code-graph/`.\n\n**Context path:** `/deep:context` -> `/speckit:plan` -> `/speckit:implement`\n**Research:** `/deep:research` -> `/speckit:plan` -> `/speckit:implement`\n**Review:** `/deep:review` -> (if issues) `/speckit:plan` -> `/speckit:implement`\n\n</system-reminder>","metadata":{"preview":"# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# DEEP REVIEW: AUTONOMOUS DEEP REVIEW LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# DEEP REVIEW: AUTONOMOUS DEEP REVIEW LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nrole: Deep Review Loop Manager\npurpose: Iterative code/spec review with convergence detection across review dimensions\naction: Run deep-review loop from initialization through synthesis\noperating_mode:\n  workflow: iterative_loop\n  workflow_compliance: MANDATORY\n  workflow_execution: autonomous\n  approvals: none\n  tracking: progressive_review_state\n  validation: convergence_detection\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# OPERATING PRINCIPLES\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\noperating_principles:","truncated":true,"loaded":["/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/CONTEXT.md"],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml","text":"# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# DEEP REVIEW: AUTONOMOUS DEEP REVIEW LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# DEEP REVIEW: AUTONOMOUS DEEP REVIEW LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nrole: Deep Review Loop Manager\npurpose: Iterative code/spec review with convergence detection across review dimensions\naction: Run deep-review loop from initialization through synthesis\noperating_mode:\n  workflow: iterative_loop\n  workflow_compliance: MANDATORY\n  workflow_execution: autonomous\n  approvals: none\n  tracking: progressive_review_state\n  validation: convergence_detection\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# OPERATING PRINCIPLES\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\noperating_principles:\n  core: \"Fresh context per iteration + externalized state = no context degradation\"\n  approach: \"Dispatch focused review agent per dimension, evaluate convergence, repeat or stop\"\n  mandate: \"Never hold findings in memory; write everything to files. Review target is READ-ONLY.\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# USER INPUTS (from setup phase)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nuser_inputs:\n  review_target: \"[REVIEW_TARGET] - What to review. REQUIRED.\"\n  review_target_type: \"[spec-folder|skill|agent|track|files] - Target type for scope derivation. REQUIRED.\"\n  review_dimensions: \"[all|correctness,security,traceability,maintainability] - Dimensions to check. Default: all.\"\n  spec_folder: \"[SPEC_FOLDER] - Spec folder path for state files. REQUIRED.\"\n  lineage_mode: \"[auto|resume|restart] - Session lifecycle intent. Default: auto. The runtime only persists lineage events for `resume` (same sessionId, no archive) and `restart` (new sessionId, generation+1, prior review/ archived). `fork` and `completed-continue` are deferred and no longer accepted — see deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md §Lifecycle Branches.\"\n  max_iterations: 7\n  convergence_threshold: 0.10\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# CONTEXT LOADING\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\ncontext_loading:\n  trigger: \"At workflow START, before phase_init\"\n  purpose: \"Load prior review context for the target and buffer it until strategy.md exists\"\n  mcp_integration:\n    tool: memory_context\n    note: \"Call MCP tools directly - NEVER through Code Mode\"\n    parameters: { input: \"{review_target}\", mode: \"focused\", intent: \"understand\", includeContent: true }\n  when_to_skip: [\"User says 'skip context' or 'fresh start'\"]\n  behavior:\n    if_context_found: \"Store full results as prior_context plus a concise prior_context_summary; inject after strategy.md is created.\"\n    if_no_context: \"Set prior_context and prior_context_summary to 'None' and continue.\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# SKILL REFERENCE\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nskill_reference:\n  skill: deep-loop-workflows\n  skill_md: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/SKILL.md\n  references:\n    loop_protocol: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\n    state_format: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/state/state_format.md\n    convergence: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/convergence/convergence.md\n  templates:\n    config: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_config.json\n    strategy: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_strategy.md\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# AGENT CONFIGURATION\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nagent_config:\n  agent: deep-review\n  agent_file: \".opencode/agents/deep-review.md\"\n  # Canonical path. Runtime-specific directories (e.g. .claude/agents/) reference this source.\n  mode: subagent\n  model: opus\n  leaf_only: true\n  tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob]\n  mcp_servers: [mk-spec-memory]\n  tool_call_budget: { target: 9, soft_max: 12, hard_max: 13 }\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# STATE FILE PATHS\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nstate_paths:\n  # Template paths document the canonical packet layout. Runtime resolution happens via\n  # step_resolve_artifact_root plus the shared resolver, so root specs keep\n  # root-local review/ and child phases keep local review/ packet dirs.\n  # Canonical root-spec write targets remain review/deep-review-config.json,\n  # review/deep-review-state.jsonl, and review/deep-review-findings-registry.json.\n  packet_dir: \"{artifact_dir}\"\n  local_packet_dir: \"{spec_folder}/review\"\n  legacy_root_report: \"{spec_folder}/review-report.md\"\n  config: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-config.json\"\n  state_log: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-state.jsonl\"\n  findings_registry: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-findings-registry.json\"\n  strategy: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md\"\n  dashboard: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-dashboard.md\"\n  pause_sentinel: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-review-pause\"\n  lock_file: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-review.lock\"\n  prompt_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/prompts\"\n  iteration_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations\"\n  iteration_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md\"\n  # Per-iteration structured delta stream — complement to the canonical state_log\n  # append. MUST contain at least one record with `type === \"iteration\"`; variants\n  # like `\"iteration_delta\"` are silently dropped by the reducer.\n  delta_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas\"\n  delta_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas/iter-{NNN}.jsonl\"\n  review_output: \"{artifact_dir}/review-report.md\"\n  resource_map_output: \"{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md\"\n  archive_root: \"{artifact_archive_root}\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# WORKFLOW\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nworkflow:\n\n  step_resolve_artifact_root:\n    description: \"Resolve artifact directory — use fan-out lineage override when provided, else resolve from spec_folder\"\n    note: \"Root specs keep review artifacts directly in {spec_folder}/review/. Child phases and sub-phases keep local packet directories in {spec_folder}/review/{packet}/, and archives stay local at {spec_folder}/review_archive/{packet}/.\"\n    branch_on: \"config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir\"\n    if_present:\n      bind:\n        artifact_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n        artifact_root_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n        artifact_subfolder: null\n        artifact_archive_root: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}/_archive\"\n    if_absent:\n      command: \"node -e \\\"const { resolveArtifactRoot } = require('.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs'); console.log(JSON.stringify(resolveArtifactRoot('{spec_folder}', 'review')));\\\"\"\n      outputs:\n        - artifact_root_dir: \"Resolved local review owner directory\"\n        - artifact_subfolder: \"Local packet subfolder ({ownerSlug}-pt-{NN}), else null\"\n        - artifact_dir: \"Resolved review packet directory for this target\"\n        - artifact_archive_root: \"Resolved local review archive directory for this target\"\n\n  step_fanout_spawn:\n    description: \"Spawn fan-out lineages; skip and proceed to phase_init normally when single-executor\"\n    skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"\n    instructions: |\n      Fan-out mode is active. Spawn all lineages. Each lineage runs the full loop in its own\n      isolated sub-packet under {artifact_dir}/lineages/{label}/.\n      After all lineages complete, jump directly to phase_synthesis — skip phase_init and\n      phase_main_loop entirely (those are the single-executor path). The merge step in\n      phase_synthesis will consolidate results across all lineages.\n    sub_steps:\n      step_fanout_spawn_cli:\n        description: \"Spawn all CLI lineages in capped worker pool\"\n        skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors with kind != 'native'\"\n        command: |\n          node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs \\\n            --spec-folder {spec_folder} \\\n            --loop-type review \\\n            --fanout-config-json '{config.fanout_json}' \\\n            --base-artifact-dir {artifact_dir}\n        working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n        wait_for_completion: true\n      step_fanout_spawn_native:\n        description: \"Dispatch each native lineage as a sequential deep-review sub-agent\"\n        skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors with kind == 'native'\"\n        for_each: \"lineage in expanded native entries of config.fanout\"\n        dispatch:\n          agent: deep-review\n          model: opus\n          context: |\n            Execute the deep-review loop with these parameters:\n              spec_folder: {spec_folder}\n              config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir: {artifact_dir}/lineages/{lineage.label}\n              session_id: fanout-{lineage.label}-{fanout_run_id}\n              executor: native\n            Run to convergence. Write all outputs to the override directory.\n        wait_for_completion: true\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # PHASE 1: INITIALIZATION\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  phase_init:\n    purpose: Create all state files for the review session and resolve review scope\n    steps:\n\n      step_preflight_contract:\n        action: \"Validate required setup bindings and executable workflow contract before any file writes\"\n        verify:\n          - required_values_present: [review_target, review_target_type, review_dimensions, spec_folder, max_iterations, convergence_threshold]\n          - spec_folder_is_within: \"specs/ or .opencode/specs/ (canonicalize alias roots before validation)\"\n          - unresolved_placeholders: \"FAIL if any user-facing template references placeholders not produced by earlier steps\"\n          - tool_contract: \"FAIL if executable steps reference tools outside the command allowlist\"\n        on_fail: \"Halt with STATUS=FAIL and report the missing binding or unsupported contract reference\"\n\n      step_create_directories:\n        action: \"Create spec folder and canonical review packet directories if they don't exist\"\n        command: \"mkdir -p {state_paths.prompt_dir} {state_paths.iteration_dir} {state_paths.delta_dir}\"\n\n      step_detect_resource_map:\n        action: \"Detect resource-map.md before config creation so init can persist coverage-gate state\"\n        inspect:\n          - \"{spec_folder}/resource-map.md\"\n        classify:\n          present: \"resource-map.md exists at init\"\n          absent: \"resource-map.md does not exist at init\"\n        outputs:\n          - resource_map_present: \"Boolean true when {spec_folder}/resource-map.md exists, else false\"\n          - resource_map_known_context: \"When present: concise resource-map snapshot for Known Context and charter framing. When absent: 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n\n      step_migrate_legacy_review_state:\n        action: \"Rehome legacy review artifacts into review/iterations before session classification\"\n        detect:\n          canonical_review_state:\n            - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n            - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n            - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n            - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n          legacy_review_state:\n            - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json\"\n            - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl\"\n            - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md\"\n            - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-dashboard.md\"\n            - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/iteration-*.md\"\n            - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/.deep-research-pause\"\n            - \"{state_paths.local_packet_dir}/iteration-*.md\"\n            - \"{state_paths.legacy_root_report}\"\n          legacy_review_markers:\n            - \"scratch/deep-review-strategy.md exists\"\n            - \"scratch/deep-research-config.json declares mode == 'review' OR scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl contains mode == 'review'\"\n        migrate_only:\n          - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json -> {state_paths.config}\"\n          - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl -> {state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md -> {state_paths.strategy}\"\n          - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-dashboard.md -> {state_paths.dashboard}\"\n          - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/iteration-*.md -> {state_paths.iteration_dir}/\"\n          - \"{spec_folder}/scratch/.deep-research-pause -> {state_paths.pause_sentinel}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.local_packet_dir}/iteration-*.md -> {state_paths.iteration_dir}/\"\n          - \"{state_paths.legacy_root_report} -> {state_paths.review_output}\"\n        on_canonical_present: \"Leave canonical review/ state untouched and do not overwrite it with legacy scratch artifacts.\"\n        on_legacy_detected: \"Move only the review-specific whitelist, append a migration event to the canonical JSONL, and leave unrelated scratch files untouched.\"\n        on_conflict: \"If canonical review/ state and legacy scratch review state both exist but disagree, halt for operator repair instead of merging contradictory state.\"\n        command: \"mkdir -p {state_paths.iteration_dir} && if [ ! -e {state_paths.config} ] && [ ! -e {state_paths.state_log} ] && [ ! -e {state_paths.strategy} ] && [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md ] && ( [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json ] || [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl ] ); then [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-config.json {state_paths.config}; [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-research-state.jsonl {state_paths.state_log}; [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-strategy.md {state_paths.strategy}; [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-dashboard.md ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/deep-review-dashboard.md {state_paths.dashboard}; find {spec_folder}/scratch -maxdepth 1 -name 'iteration-*.md' -exec mv {} {state_paths.iteration_dir}/ \\\\; ; [ -e {spec_folder}/scratch/.deep-research-pause ] && mv {spec_folder}/scratch/.deep-research-pause {state_paths.pause_sentinel}; [ -e {state_paths.legacy_root_report} ] && mv {state_paths.legacy_root_report} {state_paths.review_output}; if [ -e {state_paths.state_log} ]; then printf '%s\\n' '{\\\"type\\\":\\\"event\\\",\\\"event\\\":\\\"migration\\\",\\\"mode\\\":\\\"review\\\",\\\"legacyArtifacts\\\":[\\\"deep-research-config.json\\\",\\\"deep-research-state.jsonl\\\",\\\".deep-research-pause\\\"],\\\"canonicalArtifacts\\\":[\\\"deep-review-config.json\\\",\\\"deep-review-state.jsonl\\\",\\\".deep-review-pause\\\"],\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\\\"}' >> {state_paths.state_log}; fi; fi; find {state_paths.local_packet_dir} -maxdepth 1 -name 'iteration-*.md' -exec mv {} {state_paths.iteration_dir}/ \\\\; 2>/dev/null || true\"\n\n      step_acquire_lock:\n        action: \"Acquire the single-writer advisory lock before session classification\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs acquire --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --packet-id {spec_folder}\"\n        on_acquire: \"Capture ownerPid from the JSON output and reuse it for every release below. If acquired=false, fail closed — another deep-review run already holds this packet.\"\n        note: \"Uses the promoted deep-loop-runtime loop-lock CLI (single source of truth: stale-lock reclaim, clean owner-scoped release). macOS/BSD locking is advisory — best-effort single-writer, not a hard mutex across host calls; stale-lock override is confirm-only or explicit recovery-only.\"\n        # Lock-cleanup contract: the lock file MUST be released on every terminal exit path that follows acquisition.\n        # Runtimes honoring step_acquire_lock are required to perform this cleanup before halting or pausing.\n        on_halt:\n          action: \"Release the lock before any terminal halt branch returns control\"\n          applies_to: [\"step_classify_session.on_invalid_state\", \"step_classify_session.on_completed_session\"]\n          command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; failures here are logged but do not block the halt\"\n        on_cancel:\n          action: \"Release the lock on user cancel or pause-sentinel detection before sentinel processing\"\n          command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; cancel completes regardless of cleanup result\"\n        on_workflow_exit:\n          action: \"Release the lock as the final step of any workflow exit path (success or failure)\"\n          command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; idempotent — safe to invoke when already released\"\n\n      step_classify_session:\n        action: \"Classify the session before writing files\"\n        inspect:\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        classify:\n          fresh: \"None of the three state artifacts exist\"\n          resume: \"Config, JSONL, and strategy all exist and config.mode == 'review' and agree on target/spec folder\"\n          completed-session: \"Resume artifacts exist and config.status == 'complete'\"\n          invalid-state: \"Any partial, missing, or contradictory combination\"\n        outputs:\n          - session_state: \"fresh | resume | completed-session | invalid-state\"\n        on_resume:\n          log: \"Auto-resume: state artifacts are complete and consistent. Continue the same lineage (sessionId unchanged, generation unchanged, no archive).\"\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"resume\",\"continuedFromRun\":{iteration_count},\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":null,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          skip_to: phase_loop\n        on_restart:\n          action: \"Archive the current review packet under the root-level review_archive/ tree and start a new lineage segment with a fresh sessionId and generation+1.\"\n          command: \"if [ -d {state_paths.packet_dir} ]; then mkdir -p {state_paths.archive_root} && mv {state_paths.packet_dir} {state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}; fi\"\n          set:\n            lineage_mode: \"restart\"\n            parent_session_id: \"{prior_session_id}\"\n            generation: \"{prior_generation + 1}\"\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"restarted\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{prior_session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"restart\",\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":\"{state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          skip_to: step_create_config\n        note_deferred_branches: \"fork and completed-continue are deferred and no longer runtime-supported in this release. The reducer still reads `lineageMode` from config for dashboards and analysis, but only `new`, `resume`, and `restart` are live. See deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md §Lifecycle Branches for the one-session contract.\"\n        on_completed_session:\n          log: \"Prior session already completed. Either archive the completed review/ tree and start a fresh session, or jump straight to synthesis with the existing artifacts.\"\n          skip_to: phase_synthesis\n        on_invalid_state:\n          halt: true\n          message: \"Existing deep-review state in review/ is incomplete or contradictory. Repair or archive the invalid review packet before continuing.\"\n        on_fresh:\n          action: \"Proceed with a new session\"\n\n      step_scope_discovery:\n        action: \"Resolve review target to a concrete file list based on target type\"\n        resolve:\n          spec-folder: |\n            1. Read spec.md, plan.md, tasks.md, checklist.md, implementation-summary.md\n            2. Discover implementation files referenced in spec artifacts\n            3. Discover test files associated with implementation\n            4. Set scope = all discovered files\n          skill: |\n            1. Read SKILL.md from .opencode/skills/{skill_name}/\n            2. Discover references/, assets/, scripts/ contents\n            3. Find agent definitions referencing this skill across runtimes\n            4. Find command entry points referencing this skill\n            5. Set scope = all discovered files\n          agent: |\n            1. Find agent definition across repo-managed runtimes (.claude/agents/, .opencode/agents/, .codex/agents/, .agents/)\n            2. Compare agent definitions for consistency\n            3. Set scope = all discovered agent files\n          track: |\n            1. List all child spec folders under specs/{track}/ or .opencode/specs/{track}/\n            2. For each: read spec.md + checklist.md\n            3. Set scope = all child spec artifacts\n          files: |\n            1. Expand glob patterns from review_target\n            2. Validate all files exist\n            3. Discover immediate cross-references (imports, links)\n            4. Set scope = expanded file list + cross-references\n        outputs:\n          - review_scope_files: \"List of all files in review scope\"\n          - cross_reference_targets: \"{ spec_paths: [...], code_paths: [...], test_paths: [...] }\"\n\n      step_order_dimensions:\n        action: \"Order review dimensions based on risk priority\"\n        algorithm: |\n          1. Iteration 0 (inventory pass): Build artifact map, identify file types, estimate complexity\n          2. Subsequent iterations follow risk-ordered deep passes:\n             correctness → security → traceability → maintainability\n          3. If review_dimensions != \"all\", filter to only requested dimensions\n          4. Derive traceability protocol plan:\n             - core: spec_code, checklist_evidence\n             - overlay: skill_agent, agent_cross_runtime, feature_catalog_code, playbook_capability\n          5. If resource_map_present, reserve at least one traceability-oriented pass to cross-check target_files from applied/T-*.md against resource-map.md and classify touched / expected-by-scope / gap / absent-from-map outcomes\n          6. Store ordered list as dimension_queue\n        outputs:\n          - dimension_queue: \"Ordered list of dimensions to review\"\n          - inventory_pass: true\n\n      step_normalize_review_dimensions:\n        action: \"Normalize reviewDimensions once during init for config + JSONL reuse\"\n        outputs:\n          - review_dimensions_normalized: \"Canonical string[] for deep-review-config.json\"\n          - review_dimensions_json: \"JSON.stringify(review_dimensions_normalized) for JSONL config record\"\n        normalize: |\n          Accept {review_dimensions} in any of these shapes and convert once:\n            - \"all\" → [\"correctness\",\"security\",\"traceability\",\"maintainability\"]\n            - \"correctness,security\" → [\"correctness\",\"security\"]\n            - [\"correctness\"] → [\"correctness\"]\n          Every element MUST be one of the four canonical dimension names.\n\n      step_create_config:\n        action: \"Create deep-review-config.json from template with review-specific fields\"\n        template: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_config.json\n        populate:\n          topic: \"Review: {review_target}\"\n          mode: \"review\"\n          sessionId: \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"\n          parentSessionId: null\n          lineageMode: \"new\"\n          generation: 1\n          continuedFromRun: null\n          reviewTarget: \"{review_target}\"\n          reviewTargetType: \"{review_target_type}\"\n          # Reuse the single normalized init-time value from step_normalize_review_dimensions.\n          reviewDimensions: \"{review_dimensions_normalized}\"\n          resource_map_present: \"{resource_map_present}\"\n          reviewScopeFiles: \"{review_scope_files}\"\n          severityThreshold: \"P2\"\n          crossReference:\n            core: [\"spec_code\", \"checklist_evidence\"]\n            overlay: [\"skill_agent\", \"agent_cross_runtime\", \"feature_catalog_code\", \"playbook_capability\"]\n          maxIterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n          # Semantic: weighted P0/P1/P2 severity ratio. See SKILL.md §\"Convergence Threshold Semantics\".\n          convergenceThreshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n          stuckThreshold: 2\n          maxDurationMinutes: 120\n          specFolder: \"{spec_folder}\"\n          # <!-- F-010-B5-04 -->\n          # Honor the parsed --no-resource-map flag from deep-review.md:71 (default true; false when flag is set).\n          # The markdown command parses $ARGUMENTS and binds {resource_map_emit} before this step runs.\n          resource_map.emit: \"{resource_map_emit}\"\n          createdAt: \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"\n          status: \"initialized\"\n          releaseReadinessState: \"in-progress\"\n          executionMode: \"auto\"\n        output: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n\n      step_create_state_log:\n        action: \"Initialize JSONL state log with config record including review fields and lineage metadata\"\n        note: \"Reuse review_dimensions_json from step_normalize_review_dimensions. Never re-normalize or wrap the raw template value.\"\n        # <!-- F-010-B5-04 -->\n        # Same parsed --no-resource-map flag honored here so config and state_log agree from line 1.\n        content: '{\"type\":\"config\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"reviewTarget\":\"{review_target}\",\"reviewTargetType\":\"{review_target_type}\",\"reviewDimensions\":{review_dimensions_json},\"resource_map_present\":{resource_map_present},\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":{resource_map_emit}},\"sessionId\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"parentSessionId\":null,\"lineageMode\":\"new\",\"generation\":1,\"continuedFromRun\":null,\"maxIterations\":{max_iterations},\"convergenceThreshold\":{convergence_threshold},\"createdAt\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"specFolder\":\"{spec_folder}\"}'\n        output: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n\n      step_create_findings_registry:\n        action: \"Initialize reducer-owned review findings registry\"\n        content: '{\"sessionId\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"generation\":1,\"lineageMode\":\"new\",\"openFindings\":[],\"resolvedFindings\":[],\"repeatedFindings\":[],\"dimensionCoverage\":{\"correctness\":false,\"security\":false,\"traceability\":false,\"maintainability\":false},\"findingsBySeverity\":{\"P0\":0,\"P1\":0,\"P2\":0},\"openFindingsCount\":0,\"resolvedFindingsCount\":0,\"convergenceScore\":0.0}'\n        output: \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n\n      step_create_strategy:\n        action: \"Create review strategy file from deep_review_strategy.md template\"\n        template: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_strategy.md\n        populate:\n          review_target: \"{review_target}\"\n          review_target_type: \"{review_target_type}\"\n          dimensions: \"{dimension_queue}\"\n          scope_files: \"{review_scope_files}\"\n          cross_reference_targets: \"{cross_reference_targets}\"\n          max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n          convergence_threshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n        output: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n\n      step_enrich_strategy_context:\n        action: \"Ensure Known Context is written only after strategy.md exists\"\n        condition: \"prior_context_found\"\n        edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        note: \"Append or replace the Known Context section with prior_context_summary and retained detail from prior_context\"\n\n      step_enrich_strategy_resource_map:\n        action: \"Inject resource-map status into Known Context after strategy.md exists\"\n        edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        note: \"When resource_map_present is true, append the resource_map_known_context snapshot and add Resource Map Coverage to the Review Charter. When false, append 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n\n      step_init_complete:\n        log: \"Initialization complete. Config, state, and strategy files created. Review scope: {review_scope_files_count} files, {dimension_queue_count} dimensions.\"\n        set: { current_iteration: 1, stuck_count: 0, p0_count: 0, p1_count: 0, p2_count: 0 }\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # PHASE 2: ITERATION LOOP\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  phase_loop:\n    purpose: Dispatch review agent iterations until convergence\n    repeat: true\n    max_repeats: \"{max_iterations}\"\n    steps:\n\n      step_read_state:\n        action: \"Read current state from JSONL, strategy, and config\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n        extract:\n          - iteration_count: \"Count lines where type === 'iteration'\"\n          - current_iteration: \"iteration_count + 1\"\n          - last_newFindingsRatio: \"Extract newFindingsRatio from last iteration record\"\n          - last_focus: \"Extract focus/dimension from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n          - ratio_prev: \"Extract newFindingsRatio from second-latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n          - ratio_latest: \"Extract newFindingsRatio from latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n          - next_dimension: \"Next uncovered dimension from dimension_queue in strategy.md\"\n          - dimensions_covered: \"List of dimensions already reviewed\"\n          - dimensions_remaining: \"List of dimensions not yet reviewed\"\n          - dimension_coverage: \"covered / total dimensions\"\n          - coverage_age: \"Iterations since dimension coverage last changed; require >= 1 before STOP\"\n          - p0_count: \"Count P0 findings across all iterations\"\n          - p1_count: \"Count P1 findings across all iterations\"\n          - p2_count: \"Count P2 findings across all iterations\"\n          - resource_map_present: \"Extract boolean from deep-review-config.json, default false\"\n          - resource_map_prompt_line: \"If resource_map_present is true, return 'Resource Map Coverage: cross-check target_files from {spec_folder}/applied/T-*.md against {spec_folder}/resource-map.md and classify only missed coverage as gaps.' Else return 'Resource Map Coverage: resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate.'\"\n          - session_id: \"Extract sessionId from deep-review-config.json\"\n          - generation: \"Extract generation from deep-review-config.json, else 1\"\n          - last_3_summaries: \"Summarize the latest 3 iteration records as 'run N: dimension (ratio, P0/P1/P2)'\"\n          - latest_status: \"Extract status from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n          - last_claim_adjudication_passed: \"Scan state.jsonl for the most recent `claim_adjudication` event; use its `passed` boolean. Default true when no event exists or when activeP0 + activeP1 == 0 (gate is vacuous without adjudicable findings).\"\n          - claim_adjudication_active_count: \"Count of active P0/P1 findings at the time of the last claim_adjudication event; 0 when none exist\"\n          - security_sensitive_fix_scope: \"Boolean true when the current review is a rerun after fixes involving security, path disclosure, auth/authz, sandboxing, env precedence, public schemas, persistence, or user-visible error payloads; derive from the latest review report, remediation notes, or planning packet when present, else false.\"\n          - fix_completeness_replay_required_rows: \"Count prior active or remediated P0/P1 findings, plus any prior security/path P2 findings, that require closed-gate replay before STOP.\"\n          - fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows: \"Count required replay rows marked PASS with file:line or command evidence and producer/consumer/matrix coverage.\"\n\n      step_check_pause_sentinel:\n        action: \"Check for pause sentinel file\"\n        check: \"Does {state_paths.pause_sentinel} exist?\"\n        if_exists:\n          set:\n            pending_stop_event: \"paused\"\n            pending_stop_reason: \"userPaused\"\n            pending_stop_detail: \"sentinel file detected\"\n          skip_to: step_normalize_pause_events\n        if_not_exists:\n          proceed: true\n\n      step_graph_convergence:\n        action: \"Evaluate coverage-graph convergence before the inline review convergence vote\"\n        inspect:\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n        transform: |\n          1. Call graph convergence on the current review lineage before the inline 3-signal vote.\n          2. Record the decision as one of CONTINUE, STOP_ALLOWED, STOP_BLOCKED.\n          3. Preserve raw graph signals and blockers for reducer rollup and blocked-stop evidence.\n          4. Normalize blockers to both JSON array and CSV forms for downstream stop handling.\n          5. Set graph_stop_blocked = true only when graph_decision == \"STOP_BLOCKED\".\n        bash: 'node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/convergence.cjs --spec-folder \"{spec_folder}\" --loop-type \"review\" --session-id \"{session_id}\"'\n        note: \"Invoke the runtime script directly. Review-side graph convergence must run before the inline review stop vote.\"\n        append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"graph_convergence\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"decision\":\"{graph_decision}\",\"signals\":{graph_signals_json},\"blockers\":{graph_blockers_json},\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n        outputs:\n          - graph_decision: \"CONTINUE | STOP_ALLOWED | STOP_BLOCKED\"\n          - graph_signals_json: \"JSON object returned by convergence.cjs\"\n          - graph_blockers_json: \"JSON array of graph blockers when present, else []\"","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":500,"totalLines":1441,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml","time":{"start":1781756713935,"end":1781756713945}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0606ee1f4d679b5d016a337329d6188191bc37a9ecce48d877"}},"id":"prt_ed8f9db9f001Genlm3GBugrCxj","sessionID":"ses_1270761dbffecw7Dfym5Wp50VJ","messageID":"msg_ed8f9ac4b0015LFGMJKspDbNZp"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781756713947,"sessionID":"ses_1270761dbffecw7Dfym5Wp50VJ","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_BM0e64hAYx8hOOXCBLhlwObW","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts/reduce-state.cjs","offset":1,"limit":500},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts/reduce-state.cjs</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: // ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\n2: // ║ Deep Review State Reducer                                                ║\n3: // ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\n4: \n5: 'use strict';\n6: \n7: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n8: // 1. IMPORTS\n9: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n10: \n11: const fs = require('node:fs');\n12: const path = require('node:path');\n13: const { emitResourceMap } = require('../../shared/synthesis/resource-map.cjs');\n14: const { resolveArtifactRoot } = require('../../../deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/artifact-root.cjs');\n15: \n16: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n17: // 2. CONSTANTS\n18: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n19: \n20: const REQUIRED_DIMENSIONS = ['correctness', 'security', 'traceability', 'maintainability'];\n21: const SEVERITY_KEYS = ['P0', 'P1', 'P2'];\n22: const SEVERITY_WEIGHTS = { P0: 10.0, P1: 5.0, P2: 1.0 };\n23: const LIVE_LINEAGE_MODES = new Set(['new', 'resume', 'restart']);\n24: \n25: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n26: // 3. HELPERS\n27: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n28: \n29: function readUtf8(filePath) {\n30:   return fs.readFileSync(filePath, 'utf8');\n31: }\n32: \n33: function writeUtf8(filePath, content) {\n34:   fs.mkdirSync(path.dirname(filePath), { recursive: true });\n35:   fs.writeFileSync(filePath, content, 'utf8');\n36: }\n37: \n38: function readJson(filePath) {\n39:   return JSON.parse(readUtf8(filePath));\n40: }\n41: \n42: function getResourceMapEmitSetting(config) {\n43:   const nested = config && typeof config === 'object'\n44:     ? (config.resource_map || config.resourceMap || null)\n45:     : null;\n46:   if (nested && typeof nested === 'object' && typeof nested.emit === 'boolean') {\n47:     return nested.emit;\n48:   }\n49:   return true;\n50: }\n51: \n52: function slugify(value) {\n53:   return value\n54:     .toLowerCase()\n55:     .replace(/[^a-z0-9]+/g, '-')\n56:     .replace(/^-+|-+$/g, '')\n57:     .slice(0, 80) || 'entry';\n58: }\n59: \n60: function normalizeText(value) {\n61:   if (value === null || value === undefined) return '';\n62:   if (typeof value !== 'string') {\n63:     try { return String(value).replace(/\\s+/g, ' ').trim(); }\n64:     catch { return ''; }\n65:   }\n66:   return value.replace(/\\s+/g, ' ').trim();\n67: }\n68: \n69: function escapeRegExp(value) {\n70:   return value.replace(/[.*+?^${}()|[\\]\\\\]/g, '\\\\$&');\n71: }\n72: \n73: function zeroSeverityMap() {\n74:   return { P0: 0, P1: 0, P2: 0 };\n75: }\n76: \n77: function isFiniteNumber(value) {\n78:   return typeof value === 'number' && Number.isFinite(value);\n79: }\n80: \n81: function normalizeSeverity(value) {\n82:   return SEVERITY_KEYS.includes(value) ? value : null;\n83: }\n84: \n85: function normalizeLineageMode(value) {\n86:   const normalized = normalizeText(value).toLowerCase();\n87:   return LIVE_LINEAGE_MODES.has(normalized) ? normalized : null;\n88: }\n89: \n90: function getNestedField(record, fieldName) {\n91:   if (!record || typeof record !== 'object') {\n92:     return undefined;\n93:   }\n94:   if (record[fieldName] !== undefined) {\n95:     return record[fieldName];\n96:   }\n97:   if (record.details && typeof record.details === 'object' && record.details[fieldName] !== undefined) {\n98:     return record.details[fieldName];\n99:   }\n100:   return undefined;\n101: }\n102: \n103: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n104: // 4. PARSERS\n105: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n106: \n107: /**\n108:  * Parse JSONL content into an array of records, preserving both iteration and\n109:  * event rows. Backward-compatible array return.\n110:  *\n111:  * @param {string} jsonlContent - Newline-delimited JSON string\n112:  * @returns {Array<Object>} Parsed records (corrupt lines silently dropped — use parseJsonlDetailed for fail-closed behavior)\n113:  */\n114: function parseJsonl(jsonlContent) {\n115:   return parseJsonlDetailed(jsonlContent).records;\n116: }\n117: \n118: /**\n119:  * Parse JSONL content and report malformed lines (fail-closed pathway).\n120:  *\n121:  * Returns both the parsed records and a corruption warning list. The reducer\n122:  * exit code is non-zero when warnings are present unless `--lenient` is passed.\n123:  *\n124:  * @param {string} jsonlContent - Newline-delimited JSON string\n125:  * @returns {{records: Array<Object>, corruptionWarnings: Array<{line: number, raw: string, error: string}>}}\n126:  */\n127: function parseJsonlDetailed(jsonlContent) {\n128:   const records = [];\n129:   const corruptionWarnings = [];\n130:   let lineNumber = 0;\n131: \n132:   for (const rawLine of jsonlContent.split('\\n')) {\n133:     lineNumber += 1;\n134:     const line = rawLine.trim();\n135:     if (!line) {\n136:       continue;\n137:     }\n138: \n139:     try {\n140:       records.push(JSON.parse(line));\n141:     } catch (error) {\n142:       corruptionWarnings.push({\n143:         line: lineNumber,\n144:         raw: rawLine.length > 200 ? `${rawLine.slice(0, 200)}...` : rawLine,\n145:         error: error instanceof Error ? error.message : String(error),\n146:       });\n147:     }\n148:   }\n149: \n150:   return { records, corruptionWarnings };\n151: }\n152: \n153: function loadDeltaPayloads(deltaDir) {\n154:   if (!fs.existsSync(deltaDir)) {\n155:     return [];\n156:   }\n157: \n158:   return fs.readdirSync(deltaDir)\n159:     .filter((fileName) => /^iter-\\d+\\.jsonl$/.test(fileName))\n160:     .sort((left, right) => left.localeCompare(right, undefined, { numeric: true }))\n161:     .map((fileName) => {\n162:       const { records, corruptionWarnings } = parseJsonlDetailed(readUtf8(path.join(deltaDir, fileName)));\n163:       if (!corruptionWarnings.length) {\n164:         return records;\n165:       }\n166:       console.warn(\n167:         `[deep-review] resource-map extractor skipped ${corruptionWarnings.length} malformed delta row(s) from ${fileName}`,\n168:       );\n169:       return records.concat(new Array(corruptionWarnings.length).fill(null));\n170:     });\n171: }\n172: \n173: function extractSection(markdown, heading) {\n174:   const pattern = new RegExp(`(?:^|\\\\n)##\\\\s+${escapeRegExp(heading)}\\\\s*\\\\n([\\\\s\\\\S]*?)(?=\\\\n##\\\\s|$)`, 'i');\n175:   const match = markdown.match(pattern);\n176:   return match ? match[1].trim() : '';\n177: }\n178: \n179: function extractSubsection(sectionText, subheading) {\n180:   const pattern = new RegExp(`(?:^|\\\\n)###\\\\s+${escapeRegExp(subheading)}[^\\\\n]*\\\\n([\\\\s\\\\S]*?)(?=\\\\n###\\\\s|\\\\n##\\\\s|$)`, 'i');\n181:   const match = sectionText.match(pattern);\n182:   return match ? match[1].trim() : '';\n183: }\n184: \n185: function extractListItems(sectionText) {\n186:   return sectionText\n187:     .split('\\n')\n188:     .map((line) => line.trim())\n189:     .filter((line) => /^([-*]|\\d+\\.)\\s+/.test(line))\n190:     .map((line) => normalizeText(line.replace(/^([-*]|\\d+\\.)\\s+/, '')))\n191:     .filter(Boolean);\n192: }\n193: \n194: /**\n195:  * Parse a finding line of the form: `- **F001**: Title — file:line — Description`\n196:  *\n197:  * @param {string} line - Raw finding bullet\n198:  * @param {string} severity - P0, P1, or P2 context\n199:  * @returns {Object|null} Structured finding or null when the line is not a finding\n200:  */\n201: function parseFindingLine(line, severity) {\n202:   const match = line.match(/^\\*\\*(F\\d+)\\*\\*\\s*:\\s*(.+?)(?:\\s+[—-]\\s+`?([^`]+?)`?)?(?:\\s+[—-]\\s+(.+))?$/);\n203:   if (!match) {\n204:     return null;\n205:   }\n206: \n207:   const [, findingId, title, evidenceRaw, description] = match;\n208:   let file = null;\n209:   let lineNumber = null;\n210: \n211:   if (evidenceRaw) {\n212:     const evidenceMatch = evidenceRaw.trim().match(/^(.+?):(\\d+)(?:[:-].*)?$/);\n213:     if (evidenceMatch) {\n214:       file = evidenceMatch[1];\n215:       lineNumber = Number(evidenceMatch[2]);\n216:     } else {\n217:       file = evidenceRaw.trim();\n218:     }\n219:   }\n220: \n221:   return {\n222:     findingId,\n223:     severity,\n224:     title: normalizeText(title),\n225:     file,\n226:     line: lineNumber,\n227:     description: normalizeText(description || ''),\n228:   };\n229: }\n230: \n231: function parseFindingsBlock(sectionText, severity) {\n232:   if (!sectionText) {\n233:     return [];\n234:   }\n235: \n236:   return sectionText\n237:     .split('\\n')\n238:     .map((line) => line.trim())\n239:     .filter((line) => /^-\\s+\\*\\*F\\d+\\*\\*/.test(line))\n240:     .map((line) => parseFindingLine(line.replace(/^-\\s+/, ''), severity))\n241:     .filter(Boolean);\n242: }\n243: \n244: /**\n245:  * Parse a single iteration markdown file into a structured review record.\n246:  *\n247:  * @param {string} iterationPath - Absolute path to an iteration-NNN.md file\n248:  * @returns {Object} Parsed iteration with focus, findings, cross-reference, and reflection fields\n249:  */\n250: function parseIterationFile(iterationPath) {\n251:   const markdown = readUtf8(iterationPath);\n252:   const runMatch = iterationPath.match(/iteration-(\\d+)\\.md$/);\n253:   const headingMatch = markdown.match(/^#\\s+Iteration\\s+\\d+\\s*[-:]\\s+(.+)$/m);\n254: \n255:   // Support both old schema (Focus/Findings/Ruled Out/Dead Ends/Assessment)\n256:   // and live schema (Dispatcher/Files Reviewed/Findings - New/Traceability Checks/\n257:   // Confirmed-Clean/Next Focus).\n258:   const focusSection = extractSection(markdown, 'Focus') || extractSection(markdown, 'Dispatcher');\n259:   const findingsSection = extractSection(markdown, 'Findings') || extractSection(markdown, 'Findings - New');\n260:   const ruledOutSection = extractSection(markdown, 'Ruled Out') || extractSection(markdown, 'Confirmed-Clean Surfaces') || extractSection(markdown, 'Confirmed-Clean');\n261:   const deadEndsSection = extractSection(markdown, 'Dead Ends') || extractSection(markdown, 'Traceability Checks');\n262:   const nextFocusSection = extractSection(markdown, 'Recommended Next Focus') || extractSection(markdown, 'Next Focus (recommendation)') || extractSection(markdown, 'Next Focus');\n263:   const assessmentSection = extractSection(markdown, 'Assessment');\n264:   const filesReviewedSection = extractSection(markdown, 'Files Reviewed');\n265: \n266:   const p0Block = extractSubsection(findingsSection, 'P0') || extractSubsection(findingsSection, 'P0 Findings');\n267:   const p1Block = extractSubsection(findingsSection, 'P1') || extractSubsection(findingsSection, 'P1 Findings');\n268:   const p2Block = extractSubsection(findingsSection, 'P2') || extractSubsection(findingsSection, 'P2 Findings');\n269: \n270:   const findings = [\n271:     ...parseFindingsBlock(p0Block, 'P0'),\n272:     ...parseFindingsBlock(p1Block, 'P1'),\n273:     ...parseFindingsBlock(p2Block, 'P2'),\n274:   ];\n275: \n276:   const dimensionsAddressed = (assessmentSection.match(/Dimensions addressed:\\s*(.+)/i) || [])[1];\n277: \n278:   return {\n279:     path: iterationPath,\n280:     run: runMatch ? Number(runMatch[1]) : 0,\n281:     focus: normalizeText(focusSection || (headingMatch ? headingMatch[1] : 'Unknown focus')),\n282:     findings,\n283:     ruledOut: extractListItems(ruledOutSection),\n284:     deadEnds: extractListItems(deadEndsSection),\n285:     nextFocus: normalizeText(nextFocusSection),\n286:     dimensionsAddressed: dimensionsAddressed\n287:       ? dimensionsAddressed.split(/[,;]/).map((value) => normalizeText(value).toLowerCase()).filter(Boolean)\n288:       : [],\n289:   };\n290: }\n291: \n292: function parseStrategyDimensions(strategyContent) {\n293:   const section = extractSection(strategyContent, '3. REVIEW DIMENSIONS (remaining)')\n294:     || extractSection(strategyContent, '3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)');\n295:   return section\n296:     .split('\\n')\n297:     .map((line) => line.trim())\n298:     .filter((line) => /^- \\[[ xX]\\]\\s+/.test(line))\n299:     .map((line) => {\n300:       const checked = /^- \\[[xX]\\]\\s+/.test(line);\n301:       const text = normalizeText(line.replace(/^- \\[[ xX]\\]\\s+/, ''));\n302:       return { checked, text };\n303:     });\n304: }\n305: \n306: function uniqueById(items) {\n307:   const seen = new Set();\n308:   const result = [];\n309: \n310:   for (const item of items) {\n311:     if (seen.has(item.findingId)) {\n312:       continue;\n313:     }\n314:     seen.add(item.findingId);\n315:     result.push(item);\n316:   }\n317: \n318:   return result;\n319: }\n320: \n321: function normalizeTransitions(transitions, defaultIteration) {\n322:   const result = [];\n323:   const seen = new Set();\n324:   const rawTransitions = Array.isArray(transitions) ? transitions : [];\n325: \n326:   for (const entry of rawTransitions) {\n327:     if (!entry || typeof entry !== 'object') {\n328:       continue;\n329:     }\n330:     const iteration = isFiniteNumber(entry.iteration) ? entry.iteration : defaultIteration;\n331:     const from = entry.from === null ? null : normalizeSeverity(entry.from);\n332:     const to = normalizeSeverity(entry.to);\n333:     if (!to) {\n334:       continue;\n335:     }\n336:     const reason = normalizeText(entry.reason || '') || 'Claim adjudication';\n337:     const key = `${iteration}|${from ?? 'null'}|${to}|${reason}`;\n338:     if (seen.has(key)) {\n339:       continue;\n340:     }\n341:     seen.add(key);\n342:     result.push({ iteration, from, to, reason });\n343:   }\n344: \n345:   return result;\n346: }\n347: \n348: function mergeTransitions(existingTransitions, incomingTransitions) {\n349:   return normalizeTransitions(\n350:     []\n351:       .concat(Array.isArray(existingTransitions) ? existingTransitions : [])\n352:       .concat(Array.isArray(incomingTransitions) ? incomingTransitions : []),\n353:     0,\n354:   );\n355: }\n356: \n357: function buildClaimAdjudicationByFinding(records) {\n358:   const adjudicationByFinding = new Map();\n359: \n360:   for (const record of records) {\n361:     if (record?.type !== 'event' || record?.event !== 'claim_adjudication') {\n362:       continue;\n363:     }\n364: \n365:     const findingId = normalizeText(getNestedField(record, 'findingId') || '');\n366:     const finalSeverity = normalizeSeverity(getNestedField(record, 'finalSeverity'));\n367:     if (!findingId || !finalSeverity) {\n368:       continue;\n369:     }\n370: \n371:     const run = isFiniteNumber(getNestedField(record, 'run'))\n372:       ? getNestedField(record, 'run')\n373:       : 0;\n374:     adjudicationByFinding.set(findingId, {\n375:       findingId,\n376:       finalSeverity,\n377:       transitions: normalizeTransitions(getNestedField(record, 'transitions'), run),\n378:       reason: normalizeText(getNestedField(record, 'reason') || ''),\n379:       run,\n380:       timestamp: normalizeText(getNestedField(record, 'timestamp') || ''),\n381:     });\n382:   }\n383: \n384:   return adjudicationByFinding;\n385: }\n386: \n387: function buildLineageState(config, records, terminalStop = null) {\n388:   const latestLifecycleEvent = records\n389:     .filter((record) => record?.type === 'event' && (record?.event === 'resumed' || record?.event === 'restarted'))\n390:     .at(-1);\n391:   const eventContinuedFromRun = latestLifecycleEvent\n392:     ? getNestedField(latestLifecycleEvent, 'continuedFromRun') ?? getNestedField(latestLifecycleEvent, 'fromIteration')\n393:     : undefined;\n394:   const latestLifecycleMode = normalizeLineageMode(getNestedField(latestLifecycleEvent, 'lineageMode') || '');\n395:   const configLineageMode = normalizeLineageMode(config.lineageMode || '');\n396:   const lineageMode = latestLifecycleMode || configLineageMode || 'new';\n397:   const configContinuedFromRun = isFiniteNumber(config.continuedFromRun)\n398:     ? config.continuedFromRun\n399:     : null;\n400:   const continuedFromRun = terminalStop\n401:     ? null\n402:     : isFiniteNumber(eventContinuedFromRun)\n403:       ? eventContinuedFromRun\n404:       : lineageMode !== 'new'\n405:         ? configContinuedFromRun\n406:         : null;\n407: \n408:   return {\n409:     sessionId: normalizeText(getNestedField(latestLifecycleEvent, 'sessionId') || '') || normalizeText(config.sessionId || '') || '',\n410:     parentSessionId: normalizeText(getNestedField(latestLifecycleEvent, 'parentSessionId') || '')\n411:       || normalizeText(config.parentSessionId || '')\n412:       || null,\n413:     lineageMode,\n414:     generation: isFiniteNumber(getNestedField(latestLifecycleEvent, 'generation'))\n415:       ? getNestedField(latestLifecycleEvent, 'generation')\n416:       : isFiniteNumber(config.generation)\n417:         ? config.generation\n418:         : 1,\n419:     continuedFromRun,\n420:   };\n421: }\n422: \n423: function buildTerminalStopState(records) {\n424:   let latestSynthesis = null;\n425:   let latestSynthesisIndex = -1;\n426:   let latestIterationIndex = -1;\n427:   let latestLifecycleIndex = -1;\n428: \n429:   records.forEach((record, index) => {\n430:     if (record?.type === 'iteration') {\n431:       latestIterationIndex = index;\n432:       return;\n433:     }\n434:     if (record?.type !== 'event') {\n435:       return;\n436:     }\n437:     if (record.event === 'synthesis_complete') {\n438:       latestSynthesis = record;\n439:       latestSynthesisIndex = index;\n440:     }\n441:     if (record.event === 'resumed' || record.event === 'restarted') {\n442:       latestLifecycleIndex = index;\n443:     }\n444:   });\n445: \n446:   if (!latestSynthesis) {\n447:     return null;\n448:   }\n449:   if (latestSynthesisIndex < Math.max(latestIterationIndex, latestLifecycleIndex)) {\n450:     return null;\n451:   }\n452: \n453:   return {\n454:     stopReason: normalizeText(getNestedField(latestSynthesis, 'stopReason') || '') || null,\n455:     totalIterations: isFiniteNumber(getNestedField(latestSynthesis, 'totalIterations'))\n456:       ? getNestedField(latestSynthesis, 'totalIterations')\n457:       : null,\n458:     timestamp: normalizeText(getNestedField(latestSynthesis, 'timestamp') || '') || null,\n459:   };\n460: }\n461: \n462: function deriveDashboardStatus(config, records, terminalStop) {\n463:   if (terminalStop) {\n464:     return 'COMPLETE';\n465:   }\n466:   // LG-0001: surface pause/recovery state. The reducer already tracks iteration,\n467:   // resume/restart, and synthesis events; userPaused and stuckRecovery were the\n468:   // gap. If the most recent loop signal is a pause or recovery event (no later\n469:   // iteration/resume that would supersede it), reflect that on the dashboard\n470:   // instead of defaulting to RUNNING.\n471:   let latestPauseStuckIndex = -1;\n472:   let latestPauseStuckKind = null;\n473:   let latestProgressIndex = -1;\n474:   (Array.isArray(records) ? records : []).forEach((record, index) => {\n475:     if (record?.type === 'iteration') {\n476:       latestProgressIndex = index;\n477:       return;\n478:     }\n479:     if (record?.type !== 'event') {\n480:       return;\n481:     }\n482:     if (record.event === 'userPaused' || record.event === 'stuckRecovery') {\n483:       latestPauseStuckIndex = index;\n484:       latestPauseStuckKind = record.event;\n485:     } else if (record.event === 'resumed' || record.event === 'restarted' || record.event === 'synthesis_complete') {\n486:       latestProgressIndex = index;\n487:     }\n488:   });\n489:   if (latestPauseStuckIndex > latestProgressIndex && latestPauseStuckKind) {\n490:     return latestPauseStuckKind === 'userPaused' ? 'PAUSED' : 'RECOVERING';\n491:   }\n492:   const rawStatus = normalizeText(config.status || '').toLowerCase() || 'initialized';\n493:   if (rawStatus === 'complete' || rawStatus === 'completed') {\n494:     return 'COMPLETE';\n495:   }\n496:   if (rawStatus === 'running') {\n497:     return 'RUNNING';\n498:   }\n499:   return rawStatus.toUpperCase();\n500: }\n\n(Showing lines 1-500 of 1853. Use offset=501 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"// ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\n// ║ Deep Review State Reducer                                                ║\n// ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\n\n'use strict';\n\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 1. IMPORTS\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nconst fs = require('node:fs');\nconst path = require('node:path');\nconst { emitResourceMap } = require('../../shared/synthesis/resource-map.cjs');\nconst { resolveArtifactRoot } = require('../../../deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/artifact-root.cjs');\n\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 2. CONSTANTS\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nconst REQUIRED_DIMENSIONS = ['correctness', 'security', 'traceability', 'maintainability'];","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts/reduce-state.cjs","text":"// ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\n// ║ Deep Review State Reducer                                                ║\n// ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\n\n'use strict';\n\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 1. IMPORTS\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nconst fs = require('node:fs');\nconst path = require('node:path');\nconst { emitResourceMap } = require('../../shared/synthesis/resource-map.cjs');\nconst { resolveArtifactRoot } = require('../../../deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/artifact-root.cjs');\n\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 2. CONSTANTS\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nconst REQUIRED_DIMENSIONS = ['correctness', 'security', 'traceability', 'maintainability'];\nconst SEVERITY_KEYS = ['P0', 'P1', 'P2'];\nconst SEVERITY_WEIGHTS = { P0: 10.0, P1: 5.0, P2: 1.0 };\nconst LIVE_LINEAGE_MODES = new Set(['new', 'resume', 'restart']);\n\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 3. HELPERS\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nfunction readUtf8(filePath) {\n  return fs.readFileSync(filePath, 'utf8');\n}\n\nfunction writeUtf8(filePath, content) {\n  fs.mkdirSync(path.dirname(filePath), { recursive: true });\n  fs.writeFileSync(filePath, content, 'utf8');\n}\n\nfunction readJson(filePath) {\n  return JSON.parse(readUtf8(filePath));\n}\n\nfunction getResourceMapEmitSetting(config) {\n  const nested = config && typeof config === 'object'\n    ? (config.resource_map || config.resourceMap || null)\n    : null;\n  if (nested && typeof nested === 'object' && typeof nested.emit === 'boolean') {\n    return nested.emit;\n  }\n  return true;\n}\n\nfunction slugify(value) {\n  return value\n    .toLowerCase()\n    .replace(/[^a-z0-9]+/g, '-')\n    .replace(/^-+|-+$/g, '')\n    .slice(0, 80) || 'entry';\n}\n\nfunction normalizeText(value) {\n  if (value === null || value === undefined) return '';\n  if (typeof value !== 'string') {\n    try { return String(value).replace(/\\s+/g, ' ').trim(); }\n    catch { return ''; }\n  }\n  return value.replace(/\\s+/g, ' ').trim();\n}\n\nfunction escapeRegExp(value) {\n  return value.replace(/[.*+?^${}()|[\\]\\\\]/g, '\\\\$&');\n}\n\nfunction zeroSeverityMap() {\n  return { P0: 0, P1: 0, P2: 0 };\n}\n\nfunction isFiniteNumber(value) {\n  return typeof value === 'number' && Number.isFinite(value);\n}\n\nfunction normalizeSeverity(value) {\n  return SEVERITY_KEYS.includes(value) ? value : null;\n}\n\nfunction normalizeLineageMode(value) {\n  const normalized = normalizeText(value).toLowerCase();\n  return LIVE_LINEAGE_MODES.has(normalized) ? normalized : null;\n}\n\nfunction getNestedField(record, fieldName) {\n  if (!record || typeof record !== 'object') {\n    return undefined;\n  }\n  if (record[fieldName] !== undefined) {\n    return record[fieldName];\n  }\n  if (record.details && typeof record.details === 'object' && record.details[fieldName] !== undefined) {\n    return record.details[fieldName];\n  }\n  return undefined;\n}\n\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 4. PARSERS\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n/**\n * Parse JSONL content into an array of records, preserving both iteration and\n * event rows. Backward-compatible array return.\n *\n * @param {string} jsonlContent - Newline-delimited JSON string\n * @returns {Array<Object>} Parsed records (corrupt lines silently dropped — use parseJsonlDetailed for fail-closed behavior)\n */\nfunction parseJsonl(jsonlContent) {\n  return parseJsonlDetailed(jsonlContent).records;\n}\n\n/**\n * Parse JSONL content and report malformed lines (fail-closed pathway).\n *\n * Returns both the parsed records and a corruption warning list. The reducer\n * exit code is non-zero when warnings are present unless `--lenient` is passed.\n *\n * @param {string} jsonlContent - Newline-delimited JSON string\n * @returns {{records: Array<Object>, corruptionWarnings: Array<{line: number, raw: string, error: string}>}}\n */\nfunction parseJsonlDetailed(jsonlContent) {\n  const records = [];\n  const corruptionWarnings = [];\n  let lineNumber = 0;\n\n  for (const rawLine of jsonlContent.split('\\n')) {\n    lineNumber += 1;\n    const line = rawLine.trim();\n    if (!line) {\n      continue;\n    }\n\n    try {\n      records.push(JSON.parse(line));\n    } catch (error) {\n      corruptionWarnings.push({\n        line: lineNumber,\n        raw: rawLine.length > 200 ? `${rawLine.slice(0, 200)}...` : rawLine,\n        error: error instanceof Error ? error.message : String(error),\n      });\n    }\n  }\n\n  return { records, corruptionWarnings };\n}\n\nfunction loadDeltaPayloads(deltaDir) {\n  if (!fs.existsSync(deltaDir)) {\n    return [];\n  }\n\n  return fs.readdirSync(deltaDir)\n    .filter((fileName) => /^iter-\\d+\\.jsonl$/.test(fileName))\n    .sort((left, right) => left.localeCompare(right, undefined, { numeric: true }))\n    .map((fileName) => {\n      const { records, corruptionWarnings } = parseJsonlDetailed(readUtf8(path.join(deltaDir, fileName)));\n      if (!corruptionWarnings.length) {\n        return records;\n      }\n      console.warn(\n        `[deep-review] resource-map extractor skipped ${corruptionWarnings.length} malformed delta row(s) from ${fileName}`,\n      );\n      return records.concat(new Array(corruptionWarnings.length).fill(null));\n    });\n}\n\nfunction extractSection(markdown, heading) {\n  const pattern = new RegExp(`(?:^|\\\\n)##\\\\s+${escapeRegExp(heading)}\\\\s*\\\\n([\\\\s\\\\S]*?)(?=\\\\n##\\\\s|$)`, 'i');\n  const match = markdown.match(pattern);\n  return match ? match[1].trim() : '';\n}\n\nfunction extractSubsection(sectionText, subheading) {\n  const pattern = new RegExp(`(?:^|\\\\n)###\\\\s+${escapeRegExp(subheading)}[^\\\\n]*\\\\n([\\\\s\\\\S]*?)(?=\\\\n###\\\\s|\\\\n##\\\\s|$)`, 'i');\n  const match = sectionText.match(pattern);\n  return match ? match[1].trim() : '';\n}\n\nfunction extractListItems(sectionText) {\n  return sectionText\n    .split('\\n')\n    .map((line) => line.trim())\n    .filter((line) => /^([-*]|\\d+\\.)\\s+/.test(line))\n    .map((line) => normalizeText(line.replace(/^([-*]|\\d+\\.)\\s+/, '')))\n    .filter(Boolean);\n}\n\n/**\n * Parse a finding line of the form: `- **F001**: Title — file:line — Description`\n *\n * @param {string} line - Raw finding bullet\n * @param {string} severity - P0, P1, or P2 context\n * @returns {Object|null} Structured finding or null when the line is not a finding\n */\nfunction parseFindingLine(line, severity) {\n  const match = line.match(/^\\*\\*(F\\d+)\\*\\*\\s*:\\s*(.+?)(?:\\s+[—-]\\s+`?([^`]+?)`?)?(?:\\s+[—-]\\s+(.+))?$/);\n  if (!match) {\n    return null;\n  }\n\n  const [, findingId, title, evidenceRaw, description] = match;\n  let file = null;\n  let lineNumber = null;\n\n  if (evidenceRaw) {\n    const evidenceMatch = evidenceRaw.trim().match(/^(.+?):(\\d+)(?:[:-].*)?$/);\n    if (evidenceMatch) {\n      file = evidenceMatch[1];\n      lineNumber = Number(evidenceMatch[2]);\n    } else {\n      file = evidenceRaw.trim();\n    }\n  }\n\n  return {\n    findingId,\n    severity,\n    title: normalizeText(title),\n    file,\n    line: lineNumber,\n    description: normalizeText(description || ''),\n  };\n}\n\nfunction parseFindingsBlock(sectionText, severity) {\n  if (!sectionText) {\n    return [];\n  }\n\n  return sectionText\n    .split('\\n')\n    .map((line) => line.trim())\n    .filter((line) => /^-\\s+\\*\\*F\\d+\\*\\*/.test(line))\n    .map((line) => parseFindingLine(line.replace(/^-\\s+/, ''), severity))\n    .filter(Boolean);\n}\n\n/**\n * Parse a single iteration markdown file into a structured review record.\n *\n * @param {string} iterationPath - Absolute path to an iteration-NNN.md file\n * @returns {Object} Parsed iteration with focus, findings, cross-reference, and reflection fields\n */\nfunction parseIterationFile(iterationPath) {\n  const markdown = readUtf8(iterationPath);\n  const runMatch = iterationPath.match(/iteration-(\\d+)\\.md$/);\n  const headingMatch = markdown.match(/^#\\s+Iteration\\s+\\d+\\s*[-:]\\s+(.+)$/m);\n\n  // Support both old schema (Focus/Findings/Ruled Out/Dead Ends/Assessment)\n  // and live schema (Dispatcher/Files Reviewed/Findings - New/Traceability Checks/\n  // Confirmed-Clean/Next Focus).\n  const focusSection = extractSection(markdown, 'Focus') || extractSection(markdown, 'Dispatcher');\n  const findingsSection = extractSection(markdown, 'Findings') || extractSection(markdown, 'Findings - New');\n  const ruledOutSection = extractSection(markdown, 'Ruled Out') || extractSection(markdown, 'Confirmed-Clean Surfaces') || extractSection(markdown, 'Confirmed-Clean');\n  const deadEndsSection = extractSection(markdown, 'Dead Ends') || extractSection(markdown, 'Traceability Checks');\n  const nextFocusSection = extractSection(markdown, 'Recommended Next Focus') || extractSection(markdown, 'Next Focus (recommendation)') || extractSection(markdown, 'Next Focus');\n  const assessmentSection = extractSection(markdown, 'Assessment');\n  const filesReviewedSection = extractSection(markdown, 'Files Reviewed');\n\n  const p0Block = extractSubsection(findingsSection, 'P0') || extractSubsection(findingsSection, 'P0 Findings');\n  const p1Block = extractSubsection(findingsSection, 'P1') || extractSubsection(findingsSection, 'P1 Findings');\n  const p2Block = extractSubsection(findingsSection, 'P2') || extractSubsection(findingsSection, 'P2 Findings');\n\n  const findings = [\n    ...parseFindingsBlock(p0Block, 'P0'),\n    ...parseFindingsBlock(p1Block, 'P1'),\n    ...parseFindingsBlock(p2Block, 'P2'),\n  ];\n\n  const dimensionsAddressed = (assessmentSection.match(/Dimensions addressed:\\s*(.+)/i) || [])[1];\n\n  return {\n    path: iterationPath,\n    run: runMatch ? Number(runMatch[1]) : 0,\n    focus: normalizeText(focusSection || (headingMatch ? headingMatch[1] : 'Unknown focus')),\n    findings,\n    ruledOut: extractListItems(ruledOutSection),\n    deadEnds: extractListItems(deadEndsSection),\n    nextFocus: normalizeText(nextFocusSection),\n    dimensionsAddressed: dimensionsAddressed\n      ? dimensionsAddressed.split(/[,;]/).map((value) => normalizeText(value).toLowerCase()).filter(Boolean)\n      : [],\n  };\n}\n\nfunction parseStrategyDimensions(strategyContent) {\n  const section = extractSection(strategyContent, '3. REVIEW DIMENSIONS (remaining)')\n    || extractSection(strategyContent, '3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)');\n  return section\n    .split('\\n')\n    .map((line) => line.trim())\n    .filter((line) => /^- \\[[ xX]\\]\\s+/.test(line))\n    .map((line) => {\n      const checked = /^- \\[[xX]\\]\\s+/.test(line);\n      const text = normalizeText(line.replace(/^- \\[[ xX]\\]\\s+/, ''));\n      return { checked, text };\n    });\n}\n\nfunction uniqueById(items) {\n  const seen = new Set();\n  const result = [];\n\n  for (const item of items) {\n    if (seen.has(item.findingId)) {\n      continue;\n    }\n    seen.add(item.findingId);\n    result.push(item);\n  }\n\n  return result;\n}\n\nfunction normalizeTransitions(transitions, defaultIteration) {\n  const result = [];\n  const seen = new Set();\n  const rawTransitions = Array.isArray(transitions) ? transitions : [];\n\n  for (const entry of rawTransitions) {\n    if (!entry || typeof entry !== 'object') {\n      continue;\n    }\n    const iteration = isFiniteNumber(entry.iteration) ? entry.iteration : defaultIteration;\n    const from = entry.from === null ? null : normalizeSeverity(entry.from);\n    const to = normalizeSeverity(entry.to);\n    if (!to) {\n      continue;\n    }\n    const reason = normalizeText(entry.reason || '') || 'Claim adjudication';\n    const key = `${iteration}|${from ?? 'null'}|${to}|${reason}`;\n    if (seen.has(key)) {\n      continue;\n    }\n    seen.add(key);\n    result.push({ iteration, from, to, reason });\n  }\n\n  return result;\n}\n\nfunction mergeTransitions(existingTransitions, incomingTransitions) {\n  return normalizeTransitions(\n    []\n      .concat(Array.isArray(existingTransitions) ? existingTransitions : [])\n      .concat(Array.isArray(incomingTransitions) ? incomingTransitions : []),\n    0,\n  );\n}\n\nfunction buildClaimAdjudicationByFinding(records) {\n  const adjudicationByFinding = new Map();\n\n  for (const record of records) {\n    if (record?.type !== 'event' || record?.event !== 'claim_adjudication') {\n      continue;\n    }\n\n    const findingId = normalizeText(getNestedField(record, 'findingId') || '');\n    const finalSeverity = normalizeSeverity(getNestedField(record, 'finalSeverity'));\n    if (!findingId || !finalSeverity) {\n      continue;\n    }\n\n    const run = isFiniteNumber(getNestedField(record, 'run'))\n      ? getNestedField(record, 'run')\n      : 0;\n    adjudicationByFinding.set(findingId, {\n      findingId,\n      finalSeverity,\n      transitions: normalizeTransitions(getNestedField(record, 'transitions'), run),\n      reason: normalizeText(getNestedField(record, 'reason') || ''),\n      run,\n      timestamp: normalizeText(getNestedField(record, 'timestamp') || ''),\n    });\n  }\n\n  return adjudicationByFinding;\n}\n\nfunction buildLineageState(config, records, terminalStop = null) {\n  const latestLifecycleEvent = records\n    .filter((record) => record?.type === 'event' && (record?.event === 'resumed' || record?.event === 'restarted'))\n    .at(-1);\n  const eventContinuedFromRun = latestLifecycleEvent\n    ? getNestedField(latestLifecycleEvent, 'continuedFromRun') ?? getNestedField(latestLifecycleEvent, 'fromIteration')\n    : undefined;\n  const latestLifecycleMode = normalizeLineageMode(getNestedField(latestLifecycleEvent, 'lineageMode') || '');\n  const configLineageMode = normalizeLineageMode(config.lineageMode || '');\n  const lineageMode = latestLifecycleMode || configLineageMode || 'new';\n  const configContinuedFromRun = isFiniteNumber(config.continuedFromRun)\n    ? config.continuedFromRun\n    : null;\n  const continuedFromRun = terminalStop\n    ? null\n    : isFiniteNumber(eventContinuedFromRun)\n      ? eventContinuedFromRun\n      : lineageMode !== 'new'\n        ? configContinuedFromRun\n        : null;\n\n  return {\n    sessionId: normalizeText(getNestedField(latestLifecycleEvent, 'sessionId') || '') || normalizeText(config.sessionId || '') || '',\n    parentSessionId: normalizeText(getNestedField(latestLifecycleEvent, 'parentSessionId') || '')\n      || normalizeText(config.parentSessionId || '')\n      || null,\n    lineageMode,\n    generation: isFiniteNumber(getNestedField(latestLifecycleEvent, 'generation'))\n      ? getNestedField(latestLifecycleEvent, 'generation')\n      : isFiniteNumber(config.generation)\n        ? config.generation\n        : 1,\n    continuedFromRun,\n  };\n}\n\nfunction buildTerminalStopState(records) {\n  let latestSynthesis = null;\n  let latestSynthesisIndex = -1;\n  let latestIterationIndex = -1;\n  let latestLifecycleIndex = -1;\n\n  records.forEach((record, index) => {\n    if (record?.type === 'iteration') {\n      latestIterationIndex = index;\n      return;\n    }\n    if (record?.type !== 'event') {\n      return;\n    }\n    if (record.event === 'synthesis_complete') {\n      latestSynthesis = record;\n      latestSynthesisIndex = index;\n    }\n    if (record.event === 'resumed' || record.event === 'restarted') {\n      latestLifecycleIndex = index;\n    }\n  });\n\n  if (!latestSynthesis) {\n    return null;\n  }\n  if (latestSynthesisIndex < Math.max(latestIterationIndex, latestLifecycleIndex)) {\n    return null;\n  }\n\n  return {\n    stopReason: normalizeText(getNestedField(latestSynthesis, 'stopReason') || '') || null,\n    totalIterations: isFiniteNumber(getNestedField(latestSynthesis, 'totalIterations'))\n      ? getNestedField(latestSynthesis, 'totalIterations')\n      : null,\n    timestamp: normalizeText(getNestedField(latestSynthesis, 'timestamp') || '') || null,\n  };\n}\n\nfunction deriveDashboardStatus(config, records, terminalStop) {\n  if (terminalStop) {\n    return 'COMPLETE';\n  }\n  // LG-0001: surface pause/recovery state. The reducer already tracks iteration,\n  // resume/restart, and synthesis events; userPaused and stuckRecovery were the\n  // gap. If the most recent loop signal is a pause or recovery event (no later\n  // iteration/resume that would supersede it), reflect that on the dashboard\n  // instead of defaulting to RUNNING.\n  let latestPauseStuckIndex = -1;\n  let latestPauseStuckKind = null;\n  let latestProgressIndex = -1;\n  (Array.isArray(records) ? records : []).forEach((record, index) => {\n    if (record?.type === 'iteration') {\n      latestProgressIndex = index;\n      return;\n    }\n    if (record?.type !== 'event') {\n      return;\n    }\n    if (record.event === 'userPaused' || record.event === 'stuckRecovery') {\n      latestPauseStuckIndex = index;\n      latestPauseStuckKind = record.event;\n    } else if (record.event === 'resumed' || record.event === 'restarted' || record.event === 'synthesis_complete') {\n      latestProgressIndex = index;\n    }\n  });\n  if (latestPauseStuckIndex > latestProgressIndex && latestPauseStuckKind) {\n    return latestPauseStuckKind === 'userPaused' ? 'PAUSED' : 'RECOVERING';\n  }\n  const rawStatus = normalizeText(config.status || '').toLowerCase() || 'initialized';\n  if (rawStatus === 'complete' || rawStatus === 'completed') {\n    return 'COMPLETE';\n  }\n  if (rawStatus === 'running') {\n    return 'RUNNING';\n  }\n  return rawStatus.toUpperCase();\n}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":500,"totalLines":1853,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts/reduce-state.cjs","time":{"start":1781756713937,"end":1781756713947}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0606ee1f4d679b5d016a337329d6208191a784dbe50229acd3"}},"id":"prt_ed8f9dbd0001vG2p0KxEdDCNwg","sessionID":"ses_1270761dbffecw7Dfym5Wp50VJ","messageID":"msg_ed8f9ac4b0015LFGMJKspDbNZp"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781756713966,"sessionID":"ses_1270761dbffecw7Dfym5Wp50VJ","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_Uw2rrCK5q6OzDtVJ2jz65odS","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_config.json","offset":1,"limit":2000},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_config.json</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\n2:   \"topic\": \"\",\n3:   \"sessionId\": \"\",\n4:   \"parentSessionId\": null,\n5:   \"lineageMode\": \"new\",\n6:   \"generation\": 1,\n7:   \"continuedFromRun\": null,\n8:   \"migrationWindowEndsAt\": \"\",\n9:   \"maxIterations\": 7,\n10:   \"convergenceThreshold\": 0.10,\n11:   \"stuckThreshold\": 2,\n12:   \"maxDurationMinutes\": 120,\n13:   \"maxToolCallsPerIteration\": 12,\n14:   \"maxMinutesPerIteration\": 10,\n15:   \"progressiveSynthesis\": false,\n16:   \"specFolder\": \"\",\n17:   \"createdAt\": \"\",\n18:   \"status\": \"initialized\",\n19:   \"releaseReadinessState\": \"in-progress\",\n20:   \"executionMode\": \"auto\",\n21:   \"executor\": {\n22:     \"kind\": \"native\",\n23:     \"model\": null,\n24:     \"reasoningEffort\": null,\n25:     \"serviceTier\": null,\n26:     \"sandboxMode\": null,\n27:     \"timeoutSeconds\": 900\n28:   },\n29:   \"mode\": \"review\",\n30:   \"reviewTarget\": \"\",\n31:   \"reviewTargetType\": \"spec-folder\",\n32:   \"reviewDimensions\": [\n33:     \"correctness\",\n34:     \"security\",\n35:     \"traceability\",\n36:     \"maintainability\"\n37:   ],\n38:   \"severityThreshold\": \"P2\",\n39:   \"crossReference\": {\n40:     \"core\": [\n41:       \"spec_code\",\n42:       \"checklist_evidence\"\n43:     ],\n44:     \"overlay\": [\n45:       \"skill_agent\",\n46:       \"agent_cross_runtime\",\n47:       \"feature_catalog_code\",\n48:       \"playbook_capability\"\n49:     ]\n50:   },\n51:   \"qualityGateThreshold\": true,\n52:   \"runtimeCapabilityResolver\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts/runtime-capabilities.cjs\",\n53:   \"reducerScriptPath\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts/reduce-state.cjs\",\n54:   \"fileProtection\": {\n55:     \"deep-review-config.json\": \"immutable\",\n56:     \"deep-review-state.jsonl\": \"append-only\",\n57:     \"deep-review-findings-registry.json\": \"auto-generated\",\n58:     \"deep-review-strategy.md\": \"mutable\",\n59:     \"deep-review-dashboard.md\": \"auto-generated\",\n60:     \".deep-review-pause\": \"operator-controlled\",\n61:     \"review-report.md\": \"mutable\",\n62:     \"review-report-v*.md\": \"write-once\",\n63:     \"iteration-*.md\": \"write-once\"\n64:   },\n65:   \"reducer\": {\n66:     \"enabled\": true,\n67:     \"inputs\": [\n68:       \"latestJSONLDelta\",\n69:       \"newIterationFile\",\n70:       \"priorReducedState\"\n71:     ],\n72:     \"outputs\": [\n73:       \"findingsRegistry\",\n74:       \"dashboardMetrics\",\n75:       \"strategyUpdates\"\n76:     ],\n77:     \"metrics\": [\n78:       \"dimensionsCovered\",\n79:       \"findingsBySeverity\",\n80:       \"openFindings\",\n81:       \"resolvedFindings\",\n82:       \"convergenceScore\"\n83:     ]\n84:   },\n85:   \"_optimizerManaged\": {\n86:     \"description\": \"Fields managed by the offline loop optimizer (042.004). See optimizer-manifest.json for the canonical tunable/locked field registry.\",\n87:     \"manifestPath\": \".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/optimizer/optimizer-manifest.json\",\n88:     \"tunableFields\": [\"convergenceThreshold\", \"stuckThreshold\", \"maxIterations\"],\n89:     \"lockedFields\": [\"lineageMode\", \"reducer\", \"fileProtection\", \"sessionId\", \"mode\", \"reviewDimensions\"],\n90:     \"promotionMode\": \"advisory-only\"\n91:   }\n92: }\n\n(End of file - total 92 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\n  \"topic\": \"\",\n  \"sessionId\": \"\",\n  \"parentSessionId\": null,\n  \"lineageMode\": \"new\",\n  \"generation\": 1,\n  \"continuedFromRun\": null,\n  \"migrationWindowEndsAt\": \"\",\n  \"maxIterations\": 7,\n  \"convergenceThreshold\": 0.10,\n  \"stuckThreshold\": 2,\n  \"maxDurationMinutes\": 120,\n  \"maxToolCallsPerIteration\": 12,\n  \"maxMinutesPerIteration\": 10,\n  \"progressiveSynthesis\": false,\n  \"specFolder\": \"\",\n  \"createdAt\": \"\",\n  \"status\": \"initialized\",\n  \"releaseReadinessState\": \"in-progress\",\n  \"executionMode\": \"auto\",","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_config.json","text":"{\n  \"topic\": \"\",\n  \"sessionId\": \"\",\n  \"parentSessionId\": null,\n  \"lineageMode\": \"new\",\n  \"generation\": 1,\n  \"continuedFromRun\": null,\n  \"migrationWindowEndsAt\": \"\",\n  \"maxIterations\": 7,\n  \"convergenceThreshold\": 0.10,\n  \"stuckThreshold\": 2,\n  \"maxDurationMinutes\": 120,\n  \"maxToolCallsPerIteration\": 12,\n  \"maxMinutesPerIteration\": 10,\n  \"progressiveSynthesis\": false,\n  \"specFolder\": \"\",\n  \"createdAt\": \"\",\n  \"status\": \"initialized\",\n  \"releaseReadinessState\": \"in-progress\",\n  \"executionMode\": \"auto\",\n  \"executor\": {\n    \"kind\": \"native\",\n    \"model\": null,\n    \"reasoningEffort\": null,\n    \"serviceTier\": null,\n    \"sandboxMode\": null,\n    \"timeoutSeconds\": 900\n  },\n  \"mode\": \"review\",\n  \"reviewTarget\": \"\",\n  \"reviewTargetType\": \"spec-folder\",\n  \"reviewDimensions\": [\n    \"correctness\",\n    \"security\",\n    \"traceability\",\n    \"maintainability\"\n  ],\n  \"severityThreshold\": \"P2\",\n  \"crossReference\": {\n    \"core\": [\n      \"spec_code\",\n      \"checklist_evidence\"\n    ],\n    \"overlay\": [\n      \"skill_agent\",\n      \"agent_cross_runtime\",\n      \"feature_catalog_code\",\n      \"playbook_capability\"\n    ]\n  },\n  \"qualityGateThreshold\": true,\n  \"runtimeCapabilityResolver\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts/runtime-capabilities.cjs\",\n  \"reducerScriptPath\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/scripts/reduce-state.cjs\",\n  \"fileProtection\": {\n    \"deep-review-config.json\": \"immutable\",\n    \"deep-review-state.jsonl\": \"append-only\",\n    \"deep-review-findings-registry.json\": \"auto-generated\",\n    \"deep-review-strategy.md\": \"mutable\",\n    \"deep-review-dashboard.md\": \"auto-generated\",\n    \".deep-review-pause\": \"operator-controlled\",\n    \"review-report.md\": \"mutable\",\n    \"review-report-v*.md\": \"write-once\",\n    \"iteration-*.md\": \"write-once\"\n  },\n  \"reducer\": {\n    \"enabled\": true,\n    \"inputs\": [\n      \"latestJSONLDelta\",\n      \"newIterationFile\",\n      \"priorReducedState\"\n    ],\n    \"outputs\": [\n      \"findingsRegistry\",\n      \"dashboardMetrics\",\n      \"strategyUpdates\"\n    ],\n    \"metrics\": [\n      \"dimensionsCovered\",\n      \"findingsBySeverity\",\n      \"openFindings\",\n      \"resolvedFindings\",\n      \"convergenceScore\"\n    ]\n  },\n  \"_optimizerManaged\": {\n    \"description\": \"Fields managed by the offline loop optimizer (042.004). See optimizer-manifest.json for the canonical tunable/locked field registry.\",\n    \"manifestPath\": \".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/optimizer/optimizer-manifest.json\",\n    \"tunableFields\": [\"convergenceThreshold\", \"stuckThreshold\", \"maxIterations\"],\n    \"lockedFields\": [\"lineageMode\", \"reducer\", \"fileProtection\", \"sessionId\", \"mode\", \"reviewDimensions\"],\n    \"promotionMode\": \"advisory-only\"\n  }\n}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":92,"totalLines":92,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_config.json","time":{"start":1781756713963,"end":1781756713965}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0606ee1f4d679b5d016a337329d63081919aafac6349dee69e"}},"id":"prt_ed8f9dbea001pWwIDAL1CLOeIj","sessionID":"ses_1270761dbffecw7Dfym5Wp50VJ","messageID":"msg_ed8f9ac4b0015LFGMJKspDbNZp"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781756713966,"sessionID":"ses_1270761dbffecw7Dfym5Wp50VJ","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_xXQbYkV0NR9ib6hXr3oY0kHi","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_dashboard.md","offset":1,"limit":2000},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_dashboard.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Review Dashboard\n3: description: Auto-generated review session overview, refreshed after each iteration from JSONL state and strategy.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"deep review dashboard\"\n6:   - \"review session overview\"\n7:   - \"review findings summary\"\n8:   - \"review coverage trend\"\n9: importance_tier: normal\n10: contextType: general\n11: ---\n12: \n13: # Deep Review Dashboard - Session Overview\n14: \n15: Auto-generated summary of the current review session, regenerated after every iteration evaluation from JSONL state and strategy. Never edited manually.\n16: \n17: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n18: \n19: ### Purpose\n20: \n21: Provides a compact, human-readable summary of the current review session. Serves three roles:\n22: 1. **Observability**, quick status check during long autonomous review runs\n23: 2. **Recovery surface**, second recovery channel alongside JSONL after context compaction\n24: 3. **Resume decision**, in confirm mode, shown to user before resume/restart choice\n25: \n26: ### Usage\n27: \n28: - **Location:** `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-dashboard.md`\n29: - **Generated by:** Orchestrator (step_generate_dashboard in YAML workflow)\n30: - **Data sources:** `deep-review-state.jsonl` + `deep-review-strategy.md` + `deep-review-findings-registry.json`\n31: - **Protection:** `auto-generated`, overwritten each iteration, never manually edited\n32: \n33: ---\n34: \n35: ## 2. STATUS\n36: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n37: - Target: [from config.reviewTarget]\n38: - Target Type: [from config.reviewTargetType]\n39: - Started: [from config.createdAt]\n40: - Session: [from config.sessionId] (generation [from config.generation], lineage [from config.lineageMode])\n41: - Status: [ITERATING | CONVERGING | STUCK_RECOVERY | COMPLETE]\n42: - Release Readiness: [in-progress | converged | release-blocking]\n43: - Iteration: [N] of [maxIterations]\n44: - Provisional Verdict: [PASS | CONDITIONAL | FAIL | PENDING]\n45: - hasAdvisories: [true | false]\n46: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n47: \n48: ---\n49: \n50: ## 3. FINDINGS SUMMARY\n51: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n52: - **P0 (Critical):** [N] active, [N] new this iteration, [N] upgrades, [N] resolved\n53: - **P1 (Major):** [N] active, [N] new this iteration, [N] upgrades, [N] resolved\n54: - **P2 (Minor):** [N] active, [N] new this iteration, [N] upgrades, [N] resolved\n55: - **Repeated findings:** [N]\n56: - **Dimensions covered:** [correctness, security, traceability, maintainability]\n57: - **Convergence score:** [0.00-1.00]\n58: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n59: \n60: ---\n61: \n62: ## 4. PROGRESS\n63: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n64: \n65: | # | Focus | Files | Dimensions | New P0/P1/P2 | Ratio | Status |\n66: |---|-------|-------|------------|---------------|-------|--------|\n67: | [per iteration from JSONL] |\n68: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n69: \n70: ---\n71: \n72: ## 5. COVERAGE\n73: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n74: - Files reviewed: [X] / [Y] total\n75: - Dimensions complete: [X] / 4 total\n76: - Core protocols complete: [X] / [Y] required\n77: - Overlay protocols complete: [X] / [Y] applicable\n78: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n79: \n80: ---\n81: \n82: ## 6. TREND\n83: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n84: - Severity trend (last 3): [P0:N P1:N P2:N -> P0:N P1:N P2:N -> P0:N P1:N P2:N]\n85: - New findings trend (last 3): [N -> N -> N] [increasing | stable | decreasing]\n86: - Traceability trend (last 3): [pass/partial/fail counts -> ...]\n87: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n88: \n89: ---\n90: \n91: ## 7. RESOLVED / RULED OUT\n92: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n93: - **Disproved findings:** [findings investigated and determined to be false positives]\n94: - **Dead-end review paths:** [review approaches that yielded no actionable results]\n95: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n96: \n97: ---\n98: \n99: ## 8. NEXT FOCUS\n100: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n101: [from strategy.md \"Next Focus\" section, next dimension, file set, or review lens]\n102: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n103: \n104: ---\n105: \n106: ## 9. ACTIVE RISKS\n107: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n108: - [blockers, missing coverage, unresolved contradictions, gate violations, high stuck count, declining trend, etc.]\n109: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n110: \n111: ---\n112: \n113: ## 10. EXAMPLE (POPULATED)\n114: \n115: Reference snippet showing what a rendered review dashboard looks like after iteration 4 of a 7-iteration run. Use this as a visual anchor when inspecting a live dashboard.\n116: \n117: ```markdown\n118: # Deep Review Dashboard - Session Overview\n119: \n120: ## 2. STATUS\n121: - Target: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research (skill)\n122: - Started: 2026-04-21T10:02:11+02:00\n123: - Status: ITERATING\n124: - Iteration: 4 of 7\n125: - Verdict: PENDING\n126: - Coverage: core=pass, overlay=partial\n127: \n128: ## 3. PROGRESS\n129: \n130: | # | Dimension            | Files touched | P0 | P1 | P2 | Ratio | Status     |\n131: |---|----------------------|---------------|----|----|----|-------|------------|\n132: | 1 | correctness          | 8             | 0  | 3  | 4  | 0.78  | converged  |\n133: | 2 | test-coverage        | 6             | 1  | 2  | 1  | 0.52  | converging |\n134: | 3 | cross-runtime-parity | 5             | 0  | 2  | 0  | 0.41  | converging |\n135: | 4 | observability        | 4             | 0  | 1  | 2  | 0.29  | converging |\n136: \n137: ## 6. TRACEABILITY TREND\n138: - Core protocols: spec_code=pass, checklist_evidence=pass\n139: - Overlay protocols: skill_agent=pass, agent_cross_runtime=partial\n140: - Traceability trend (last 3): 3/0/1 -> 4/0/0 -> 4/1/0\n141: \n142: ## 9. ACTIVE RISKS\n143: - 1 P0 in test-coverage dimension -- review cannot terminate PASS until resolved\n144: - agent_cross_runtime protocol partial: Codex runtime path still unverified\n145: ```\n\n(End of file - total 145 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Review Dashboard\ndescription: Auto-generated review session overview, refreshed after each iteration from JSONL state and strategy.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review dashboard\"\n  - \"review session overview\"\n  - \"review findings summary\"\n  - \"review coverage trend\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: general\n---\n\n# Deep Review Dashboard - Session Overview\n\nAuto-generated summary of the current review session, regenerated after every iteration evaluation from JSONL state and strategy. Never edited manually.\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_dashboard.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Review Dashboard\ndescription: Auto-generated review session overview, refreshed after each iteration from JSONL state and strategy.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review dashboard\"\n  - \"review session overview\"\n  - \"review findings summary\"\n  - \"review coverage trend\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: general\n---\n\n# Deep Review Dashboard - Session Overview\n\nAuto-generated summary of the current review session, regenerated after every iteration evaluation from JSONL state and strategy. Never edited manually.\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nProvides a compact, human-readable summary of the current review session. Serves three roles:\n1. **Observability**, quick status check during long autonomous review runs\n2. **Recovery surface**, second recovery channel alongside JSONL after context compaction\n3. **Resume decision**, in confirm mode, shown to user before resume/restart choice\n\n### Usage\n\n- **Location:** `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-dashboard.md`\n- **Generated by:** Orchestrator (step_generate_dashboard in YAML workflow)\n- **Data sources:** `deep-review-state.jsonl` + `deep-review-strategy.md` + `deep-review-findings-registry.json`\n- **Protection:** `auto-generated`, overwritten each iteration, never manually edited\n\n---\n\n## 2. STATUS\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n- Target: [from config.reviewTarget]\n- Target Type: [from config.reviewTargetType]\n- Started: [from config.createdAt]\n- Session: [from config.sessionId] (generation [from config.generation], lineage [from config.lineageMode])\n- Status: [ITERATING | CONVERGING | STUCK_RECOVERY | COMPLETE]\n- Release Readiness: [in-progress | converged | release-blocking]\n- Iteration: [N] of [maxIterations]\n- Provisional Verdict: [PASS | CONDITIONAL | FAIL | PENDING]\n- hasAdvisories: [true | false]\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 3. FINDINGS SUMMARY\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n- **P0 (Critical):** [N] active, [N] new this iteration, [N] upgrades, [N] resolved\n- **P1 (Major):** [N] active, [N] new this iteration, [N] upgrades, [N] resolved\n- **P2 (Minor):** [N] active, [N] new this iteration, [N] upgrades, [N] resolved\n- **Repeated findings:** [N]\n- **Dimensions covered:** [correctness, security, traceability, maintainability]\n- **Convergence score:** [0.00-1.00]\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 4. PROGRESS\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n\n| # | Focus | Files | Dimensions | New P0/P1/P2 | Ratio | Status |\n|---|-------|-------|------------|---------------|-------|--------|\n| [per iteration from JSONL] |\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 5. COVERAGE\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n- Files reviewed: [X] / [Y] total\n- Dimensions complete: [X] / 4 total\n- Core protocols complete: [X] / [Y] required\n- Overlay protocols complete: [X] / [Y] applicable\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 6. TREND\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n- Severity trend (last 3): [P0:N P1:N P2:N -> P0:N P1:N P2:N -> P0:N P1:N P2:N]\n- New findings trend (last 3): [N -> N -> N] [increasing | stable | decreasing]\n- Traceability trend (last 3): [pass/partial/fail counts -> ...]\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 7. RESOLVED / RULED OUT\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n- **Disproved findings:** [findings investigated and determined to be false positives]\n- **Dead-end review paths:** [review approaches that yielded no actionable results]\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 8. NEXT FOCUS\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n[from strategy.md \"Next Focus\" section, next dimension, file set, or review lens]\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 9. ACTIVE RISKS\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n- [blockers, missing coverage, unresolved contradictions, gate violations, high stuck count, declining trend, etc.]\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 10. EXAMPLE (POPULATED)\n\nReference snippet showing what a rendered review dashboard looks like after iteration 4 of a 7-iteration run. Use this as a visual anchor when inspecting a live dashboard.\n\n```markdown\n# Deep Review Dashboard - Session Overview\n\n## 2. STATUS\n- Target: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research (skill)\n- Started: 2026-04-21T10:02:11+02:00\n- Status: ITERATING\n- Iteration: 4 of 7\n- Verdict: PENDING\n- Coverage: core=pass, overlay=partial\n\n## 3. PROGRESS\n\n| # | Dimension            | Files touched | P0 | P1 | P2 | Ratio | Status     |\n|---|----------------------|---------------|----|----|----|-------|------------|\n| 1 | correctness          | 8             | 0  | 3  | 4  | 0.78  | converged  |\n| 2 | test-coverage        | 6             | 1  | 2  | 1  | 0.52  | converging |\n| 3 | cross-runtime-parity | 5             | 0  | 2  | 0  | 0.41  | converging |\n| 4 | observability        | 4             | 0  | 1  | 2  | 0.29  | converging |\n\n## 6. TRACEABILITY TREND\n- Core protocols: spec_code=pass, checklist_evidence=pass\n- Overlay protocols: skill_agent=pass, agent_cross_runtime=partial\n- Traceability trend (last 3): 3/0/1 -> 4/0/0 -> 4/1/0\n\n## 9. ACTIVE RISKS\n- 1 P0 in test-coverage dimension -- review cannot terminate PASS until resolved\n- agent_cross_runtime protocol partial: Codex runtime path still unverified\n```","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":145,"totalLines":145,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_dashboard.md","time":{"start":1781756713961,"end":1781756713966}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0606ee1f4d679b5d016a337329d62c8191b43e6c831c90e4a9"}},"id":"prt_ed8f9dbd8001VwGOvtBNZKBY5Z","sessionID":"ses_1270761dbffecw7Dfym5Wp50VJ","messageID":"msg_ed8f9ac4b0015LFGMJKspDbNZp"}}
